{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}A genealogy of Jesus Christ, a descendant of David and Abraham.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Abraham was the father of Isaac, Isaac of Jacob, Jacob of Judah and his brothers,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Judah of Perez and Zerah, whose mother was Tamar, Perez of Hezron, Hezron of Aram,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Aram of Aminadab, Aminadab of Nahshon, Nahshon of Salmon,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Salmon of Boaz, whose mother was Rahab, Boaz of Obed, whose mother was Ruth, Obed of Jesse,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Jesse of David the King. David was the father of Solomon, whose mother was Uriah\uc1\u8217*s widow,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Solomon of Rehoboam, Rehoboam of Abijah, Abijah of Asa,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Asa of Jehoshaphat, Jehoshaphat of Joram, Joram of Uzziah,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Uzziah of Jotham, Jotham of Ahaz, Ahaz of Hezekiah,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Hezekiah of Manasseh, Manasseh of Amon, Amon of Josiah,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Josiah of Jechoniah and his brothers, at the time of the Exile to Babylon.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}After the Exile to Babylon \uc1\u8211* Jechoniah was the father of Salathiel, Salathiel of Zerubbabel,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Zerubbabel of Abiud, Abiud of Eliakim, Eliakim of Azor,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Azor of Zadok, Zadok of Achim, Achim of Eliud,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Eliud of Eleazar, Eleazar of Matthan, Matthan of Jacob,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Jacob of Joseph, the husband of Mary, who was the mother of Jesus, who is called \uc1\u8216*Christ\uc1\u8217*.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}So the whole number of generations from Abraham to David is fourteen; from David to the Exile to Babylon fourteen; and from the Exile to Babylon to the Christ fourteen.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}This is how Jesus Christ was born:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 His mother Mary was engaged to Joseph, but, before the marriage took place, she found herself to be pregnant by the power of the Holy Spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Her husband, Joseph, was a just man and, since he did not want to disgrace her publicly, he resolved to put an end to their engagement privately.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}He had been thinking this over, when an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 \uc1\u8220*Joseph, son of David,\uc1\u8221* the angel said, \uc1\u8220*do not be afraid to take Mary for your wife, for her child has been conceived by the power of the Holy Spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}She will give birth to a son; name him Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}All this happened in fulfillment of these words of the Lord through the prophet, where he says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8216*The virgin will conceive and will give birth to a son, and they will give him the name Immanuel\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 \uc1\u8211* a word which means \uc1\u8216*God is with us.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}When Joseph woke up, he did as the angel of the Lord had directed him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}He made Mary his wife, but they did not sleep together before the birth of her son; and to this son he gave the name Jesus.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}After the birth of Jesus at Bethlehem in Judea, in the reign of King Herod, some astrologers from the East arrived in Jerusalem, asking,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8220*Where is the newborn king of the Jews? For we saw his star in the east, and have come to worship him.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}When King Herod heard of this, he was much troubled, and so too was all Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}He called together all the chief priests and teachers of the Law in the nation, and questioned them as to where the Christ was to be born.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8220*At Bethlehem in Judea,\uc1\u8221* was their answer, \uc1\u8220*for it is said in the prophet \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8216*And you, Bethlehem in Judah\uc1\u8217*s land,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 are in no way least among the chief cities of Judah,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 for out of you will come a ruler \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 who will shepherd my people Israel.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Then Herod secretly sent for the astrologers. He found out from them the time of the appearance of the star.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Sending them to Bethlehem he said, \uc1\u8220*Go and make a careful search for the child. When you have found him, bring word back to me, so that I, too, can go and worship him.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The astrologers heard what the king had to say, and then continued their journey. The star which they had seen in the east led them on, until it reached and stood over the place where the child was.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}At the sight of the star they were filled with joy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Entering the house, they saw the child with his mother, Mary, and fell at his feet and worshiped him. Then they opened their treasure chests, and offered to the child presents of gold, frankincense, and myrrh.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}But afterward, having been warned in a dream not to go back to Herod, they returned to their own country by another road.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}After they had left, an angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph in a dream, and said, \uc1\u8220*Get up, take the child and his mother, and seek refuge in Egypt; and stay there until I tell you to return, for Herod is about to search for the child, to put him to death.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Joseph woke up, and taking the child and his mother by night, went into Egypt,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}and there he stayed until Herod\uc1\u8217*s death. This was in fulfillment of these words of the Lord in the prophet, where he says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 \uc1\u8216*Out of Egypt I called my Son.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}When Herod found out that the astrologers had tricked him, he flew into a rage. He sent and put to death all the boys in Bethlehem and the whole of that region, who were two years old or under, guided by the time which he had learned from the astrologers.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Then were fulfilled these words spoken in the prophet Jeremiah, where he says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8216*A voice was heard in Ramah,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 weeping and mourning loudly;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Rachel, weeping for her children,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 refusing all comfort for they were dead.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}But, on the death of Herod, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph in Egypt, and said,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}\uc1\u8220*Get up, take the child and his mother, and go into the Land of Israel, for those who sought to take the child\uc1\u8217*s life are dead.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}He woke up, and taking the child and his mother, went into the Land of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}But, hearing that Archelaus had succeeded his father Herod as king of Judea, he was afraid to go back there; and having been warned in a dream, he went into the part of the country called Galilee.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}There he settled in the town of Nazareth, in fulfillment of these words in the prophets \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*He will be called a Nazarene.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Preparation

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}About that time John the Baptist first appeared, proclaiming in the wilderness of Judea:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8220*Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}John was the one who was spoken of in the prophet Isaiah, where he says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 \uc1\u8216*The voice of one crying aloud in the wilderness:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 \uc1\u8220*Make ready the way of the Lord,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 make his paths straight.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}John\uc1\u8217*s clothes were made of camels\uc1\u8217* hair, with a leather strap around his waist, and his food was locusts and wild honey.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}At that time Jerusalem, and all Judea, as well as the whole district of the Jordan, went out to him{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}and were baptized by him in the Jordan River, confessing their sins.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}But when John saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees coming to receive his baptism, he said to them, \uc1\u8220*You children of snakes! Who has prompted you to seek refuge from the coming judgment?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Let your life, then, prove your repentance;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}and do not think that you can say among yourselves \uc1\u8216*Abraham is our ancestor,\uc1\u8217* for I tell you that out of these stones God is able to raise descendants for Abraham!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Already the axe is lying at the root of the trees. Therefore every tree that fails to bear good fruit will be cut down and thrown into the fire.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}I, indeed, baptize you with water to teach repentance; but he who is coming after me is more powerful than I, and I am not fit even to carry his sandals. He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}His winnowing-fan is in his hand, and he will clear his threshing-floor, and store his grain in the barn, but the chaff he will burn with a fire that cannot be put out.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then Jesus came from Galilee to the Jordan, to John, to be baptized by him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}But John tried to prevent him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 \uc1\u8220*I need to be baptized by you,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*so why have you come to me?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}\uc1\u8220*This is the way it should be for now,\uc1\u8221* Jesus answered, \uc1\u8220*because we should do everything that God requires.\uc1\u8221* So John agreed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}After the baptism of Jesus, and just as he came up from the water, the heavens opened, and he saw the Spirit of God coming down like a dove and resting on him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}and from the heavens there came a voice which said, \uc1\u8220*This is my dearly loved son, who brings me great joy.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}Then Jesus was led up into the wilderness by the Spirit to be tempted by the devil.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}And, after he had fasted for forty days and forty nights, he became hungry.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}The Tempter came to him, and said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 \uc1\u8220*If you are God\uc1\u8217*s Son, tell these stones to become loaves of bread.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}But Jesus answered, \uc1\u8220*Scripture says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 \uc1\u8216*It is not on bread alone that a person is to live, but on every word that comes from the mouth of God.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Then the devil took him to the Holy City, and, placing him on the parapet of the temple, said to him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8220*If you are God\uc1\u8217*s Son, throw yourself down, for scripture says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 \uc1\u8216*He will give his angels commands about you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and on their hands they will lift you up,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 so you do not even strike your foot against a stone.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}\uc1\u8220*Scripture also says,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus,
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 \uc1\u8220*\uc1\u8216*You must not tempt the Lord your God.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The third time, the devil took Jesus to a very high mountain, and, showing him all the kingdoms of the world and their splendor, said to him:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}\uc1\u8220*All these I will give you, if you will fall at my feet and worship me.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Then Jesus said to him, \uc1\u8220*Go away, Satan! For scripture says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 \uc1\u8216*You must worship the Lord your God, and worship him only.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Then the devil left him alone, and angels came and helped him.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Work in Galilee

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}When Jesus heard that John had been arrested, he returned to Galilee.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Afterward, leaving Nazareth, he went and settled at Capernaum, which is by the side of the sea, within the borders of Zebulun and Naphtali;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}in fulfillment of these words in the prophet Isaiah \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}\uc1\u8216*The land of Zebulun and the land of Naphtali,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 the land of the Road by the sea, and beyond the Jordan,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 with Galilee of the Gentiles \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}The people who were living in darkness
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 have seen a great light,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and, for those who were living in the shadow-land of death,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 a light has dawned!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}At that time Jesus began to proclaim \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 \uc1\u8220*Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}As Jesus was walking along the shore of the Sea of Galilee, he saw two brothers \uc1\u8211* Simon, also known as Peter, and his brother Andrew \uc1\u8211* casting a net into the sea; for they were fishermen.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}\uc1\u8220*Come and follow me,\uc1\u8221* Jesus said, \uc1\u8220*and I will teach you to fish for people.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}The two men left their nets at once and followed him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Going further on, he saw two other men who were also brothers, James, Zebedee\uc1\u8217*s son, and his brother John, in their boat with their father, mending their nets. Jesus called them,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}and they at once left their boat and their father, and followed him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Jesus went all through Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, proclaiming the good news of the kingdom, and curing every kind of disease and every kind of sickness among the people;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}and his fame spread all through Syria. They brought to him all who were ill with any form of disease, or who were suffering pain \uc1\u8211* any who were either possessed by demons, or were lunatic, or paralyzed; and he cured them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}He was followed by large crowds from Galilee, the district of the Ten Towns, Jerusalem, Judea, and from beyond the Jordan.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 5}On seeing the crowds of people, Jesus went up the hill; and, when he had taken his seat, his disciples came up to him;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and he began to teach them, saying:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}\uc1\u8220*Blessed are the poor in spirit,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Blessed are the mourners,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 for they will be comforted.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Blessed are the gentle,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 for they will inherit the earth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Blessed are those who hunger and thirst for righteousness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 for they will be satisfied.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Blessed are the merciful,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 for they will find mercy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Blessed are the pure in heart,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 for they will see God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Blessed are the peacemakers,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 for they will be called children of God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Blessed are those who have been persecuted in the cause of righteousness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8220*Blessed are you when people insult you, and persecute you, and say all kinds of evil lies about you because of me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Be glad and rejoice, because your reward in heaven will be great; this is the way they persecuted the prophets who lived before you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8220*You are salt for the world. But if salt becomes tasteless, how can it be made salty again? It is no longer good for anything, but is thrown away, and trampled underfoot.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}It is you who are the light of the world. A town that stands on a hill cannot be hidden.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}People do not light a lamp and put it under a basket, but on the lamp-stand, where it gives light to everyone in the house.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Let your light so shine before the eyes of others so that, seeing your good actions, they will praise your Father who is in heaven.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8220*Do not think that I have come to do away with the Law or the prophets; I have not come to do away with them, but to complete them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}For I tell you, until the heavens and the earth disappear, not even the smallest letter, nor one stroke of a letter, will disappear from the Law until all is done.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Whoever, therefore, breaks one of these commandments, even the least of them, and teaches others to do so, will be the least esteemed in the kingdom of heaven; but whoever keeps them, and teaches others to do so, will be esteemed great in the kingdom of heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Indeed I tell you that, unless you obey God\uc1\u8217*s commands better than of the teachers of the Law, and Pharisees, you will never enter the kingdom of heaven.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8220*You have heard that to our ancestors it was said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*You must not commit murder,\uc1\u8217* and \uc1\u8216*Whoever commits murder will be brought to trial.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}But I say to you that anyone who is angry at their brother or sister will be brought to trial; and whoever insults their brother or sister will be brought before the High Council, while whoever calls them a fool will be in danger of the fires of Gehenna.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Therefore, when presenting your gift at the altar, if even there you remember that your brother or sister has something against you,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}leave your gift there, before the altar, go and be reconciled to them, first, then come and present your gift.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Be ready to make friends with your opponent, even when you meet them on your way to the court; otherwise they might hand you over to the judge, and the judge to the judicial officer, and you will be thrown into prison.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}I tell you, you will not come out until you have paid the last cent.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}\uc1\u8220*You have heard that it was said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*You must not commit adultery.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}But I say to you that anyone who looks at a woman and desires her has already committed adultery with her in his heart.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}If your right eye causes you to sin, take it out and throw it away. It would be best for you to lose one part of your body, and not to have the whole of it thrown into Gehenna.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}And, if your right hand causes you to sin, cut it off and throw it away. It would be best for you to lose one part of your body, and not to have the whole of it go down to Gehenna.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}\uc1\u8220*It was also said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Let anyone who divorces his wife serve her with a notice of separation.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}But I say to you that anyone who divorces his wife, except on the ground of some serious sexual sin, leads to her committing adultery; while anyone who marries her after her divorce is guilty of adultery.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}Again, you have heard that our ancestors were told \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Do not break your oaths, keep your vows to the Lord.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}But I say to you that you must not swear at all, either by heaven, since that is God\uc1\u8217*s throne,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}or by the earth, since that is his footstool, or by Jerusalem, since that is the city of the Great King.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Nor should you swear by your head, since you cannot make a single hair either white or black.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Let your words be simply \uc1\u8216*Yes\uc1\u8217* or \uc1\u8216*No\uc1\u8217*; anything beyond this comes from what is evil.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}\uc1\u8220*You have heard that it was said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*An eye for an eye and a tooth for a tooth.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}But I say to you that you must not resist those who wrong you; but, if anyone strikes you on the right cheek, turn the other to them also.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}If someone sues you for your shirt, let them have your cloak as well.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}If you are forced to carry a soldier\uc1\u8217*s pack for one mile, carry it two.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}Give to anyone who asks and, if someone wants to borrow from you, do not turn them away.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}You have heard that it was said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*You must love your neighbor and hate your enemy.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}But what I tell you is this: love your enemies, and pray for those who persecute you,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}so that you may become children of your Father who is in heaven; for he causes his sun to rise on bad and good alike, and sends rain on the righteous and on the unrighteous.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}For, if you love only those who love you, what reward will you have? Even the tax collectors do this!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}And, if you only welcome your brothers and sisters, what are you doing more than others? Even the Gentiles do this!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}You, then, must become perfect \uc1\u8211* as your heavenly Father is perfect.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}\uc1\u8220*Take care not to perform your religious duties in public in order to be seen by others; if you do, your Father who is in heaven has no reward for you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Therefore, when you do acts of charity, do not have a trumpet blown in front of you, as hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets so that people will praise them. There, I tell you, is their reward!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}But, when you do acts of charity, do not let your left hand know what your right hand is doing,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}so that your charity may be secret; and your Father, who sees what is in secret, will reward you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8220*And, when you pray, you are not to behave as hypocrites do. They like to pray standing in the synagogues and at the corners of the streets, so that people will see them. There, I tell you, is their reward!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But, when one of you prays, they should go into their own room, shut the door, and pray to their Father who dwells in secret; and their Father, who sees what is secret, will reward them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}When praying, do not repeat the same words over and over again, as is done by the Gentiles, who think that by using many words they will obtain a hearing.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Do not imitate them; for God, your Father, knows what you need before you ask him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}You, therefore, should pray like this \uc1\u8211*
\par}

