{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}For, if you forgive others their offenses, your heavenly Father will forgive you also;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}but, if you do not forgive others their offenses, not even your Father will forgive your offenses.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8220*And, when you fast, do not put on gloomy looks, as hypocrites do who disfigure their faces so that they may be seen by people to be fasting. That, I tell you, is their reward!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}But, when one of you fasts, they should anoint their head and wash their face,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}so that they may not be seen by people to be fasting, but by their Father who dwells in secret; and their Father, who sees what is secret, will reward them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}\uc1\u8220*Do not store up treasures for yourselves on earth, where moth and rust destroy, and where thieves break in and steal.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}But store up treasures for yourselves in heaven, where neither moth nor rust destroys, and where thieves do not break in or steal.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}The lamp of the body is the eye. If your eye is unclouded, your whole body will be lit up;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}but, if your eye is diseased, your whole body will be darkened. And, if the inner light is darkness, how intense must that darkness be!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}No one can serve two masters, for either they will hate one and love the other, or else they will attach themselves to one and despise the other. You cannot serve both God and Money.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}\uc1\u8220*This is why I say to you, Do not be anxious about your life \uc1\u8211* what you can get to eat or drink, or about your body \uc1\u8211* what you can get to wear. Is not life more than food, and the body more than clothing?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Look at the wild birds \uc1\u8211* they neither sow, nor reap, nor gather into barns; and yet your heavenly Father feeds them! Aren\uc1\u8217*t you more precious than they?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}But which of you, by being anxious, can prolong their life a single moment?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}And why be anxious about clothing? Study the wild lilies, and how they grow. They neither toil nor spin;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}yet I tell you that even Solomon in all his splendor was not robed like one of these.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}If God so clothes even the grass of the field, which is living today and tomorrow will be thrown into the oven, won\uc1\u8217*t he much more clothe you, you of little faith?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Do not then ask anxiously \uc1\u8216*What can we get to eat?\uc1\u8217* or \uc1\u8216*What can we get to drink?\uc1\u8217* or \uc1\u8216*What can we get to wear?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}All these are the things for which the nations are seeking, and your heavenly Father knows that you need them all.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}But first seek his kingdom and the righteousness that he requires, and then all these things will be added for you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Therefore do not be anxious about tomorrow, for tomorrow will bring its own anxieties. Every day has trouble enough of its own.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 7}\uc1\u8220*Do not judge and you will not be judged.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}For, just as you judge others, you will yourselves be judged, and the standard that you use will be used for you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Why do you look at the speck of sawdust in your friend\uc1\u8217*s eye, while you pay no attention at all to the plank of wood in yours?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}How will you say to your friend \uc1\u8216*Let me take out the speck from your eye,\uc1\u8217* when all the time there is a plank in your own?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Hypocrite! Take out the plank from your own eye first, and then you will see clearly how to take out the speck from your friend\uc1\u8217*s.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8220*Do not give what is sacred to dogs; they will turn and maul you. Do not throw your pearls before pigs; they will trample them underfoot.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Ask, and it will be given to you; search, and you will find; knock, and the door will be opened to you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}For the person who asks receives, the person who searches finds, and to the door will be opened to the person who knocks.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Who among you, when their child asks them for bread, will give them a stone,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}or when they ask for a fish, will give them a snake?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}If you, then, wicked though you are, know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your Father who is in heaven give what is good to those who ask him!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}\uc1\u8220*Do to others whatever you would wish them to do to you; for that is the teaching of both the Law and the prophets.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Go in by the small gate. The road that leads to destruction is broad and spacious, and many go in by it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}For the gate is small, and the road narrow, that leads to life, and there are few who find it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}\uc1\u8220*Beware of false teachers \uc1\u8211* people who come to you in the guise of sheep, but at heart they are ravenous wolves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}By the fruit of their lives you will know them. Do people pick grapes from thorn bushes, or figs from thistles?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}So, too, every sound tree bears good fruit, while a worthless tree bears bad fruit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}A sound tree cannot produce bad fruit, nor can a worthless tree bear good fruit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Every tree that fails to bear good fruit is cut down and thrown into the fire.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}So it is by the fruit of their lives that you will know such people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Not everyone who says to me \uc1\u8216*Master! Master!\uc1\u8217* will enter the kingdom of heaven, but only he who does the will of my Father who is in heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}On that day many will say to me \uc1\u8216*Master, Master, was not it in your name that we taught, and in your name that we drove out demons, and in your name that we did many miracles?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And then I will say to them plainly \uc1\u8216*I never knew you. Go from my presence, you who live in sin.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}\uc1\u8220*Everyone, therefore, who listens to this teaching of mine and acts on it may be compared to a prudent person, who built their house on the rock.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}The rain poured down, the rivers rose, the winds blew and beat on that house, but it did not fall, for its foundations were on the rock.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Everyone who listens to this teaching of mine and does not act on it may be compared to a foolish person, who built their house on the sand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}The rain poured down, the rivers rose, the winds blew and struck against that house, and it fell with a great crash.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}By the time that Jesus had finished speaking, the crowd was filled with amazement at his teaching.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}For he taught them like one who had authority, and not like their teachers of the Law.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 8}When Jesus had come down from the hill, great crowds followed him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}He saw a leper who came up, and bowed to the ground before him, and said, \uc1\u8220*Master, if only you are willing, you are able to make me clean.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Stretching out his hand, Jesus touched him, saying as he did so, \uc1\u8220*I am willing; become clean.\uc1\u8221* Instantly he was made clean from his leprosy;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and then Jesus said to him, \uc1\u8220*Be careful not to say a word to anyone, but go and show yourself to the priest, and offer the gift directed by Moses, as evidence of your cure.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}After Jesus had entered Capernaum, a centurion in the Roman army came up to him, entreating his help.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8220*Sir,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*my manservant is lying ill at my house with a stroke of paralysis, and is suffering terribly.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}\uc1\u8220*I will come and cure him,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8220*Sir,\uc1\u8221* the centurion went on, \uc1\u8220*I am unworthy to receive you under my roof; but only speak, and my manservant will be cured.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For I myself am a man under the orders of others, with soldiers under me; and, if I say to one of them \uc1\u8216*Go,\uc1\u8217* he goes, and to another \uc1\u8216*Come,\uc1\u8217* he comes, and to my slave \uc1\u8216*Do this,\uc1\u8217* he does it.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Jesus was surprised to hear this, and said to those who were following him, \uc1\u8220*Never I tell you, in any Israelite have I met with such faith as this!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Yes, and many will come in from East and West and take their places beside Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, in the kingdom of heaven;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}while the heirs to the kingdom will be banished into the darkness outside; there, there will be weeping and grinding of teeth.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then Jesus said to the centurion, \uc1\u8220*Go now, and it will be according to your faith.\uc1\u8221* And the man was cured that very hour.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}When Jesus went into Peter\uc1\u8217*s house, he saw Peter\uc1\u8217*s mother-in-law prostrated with fever.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}On his taking her hand, the fever left her, and she rose and began to take care of him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}In the evening the people brought to Jesus many who were possessed by demons; and he drove out the spirits with a word, and cured all who were ill,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}in fulfillment of these words in the prophet Isaiah \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*He took our infirmities on himself, and bore the burden of our diseases.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Seeing a crowd around him, Jesus gave orders to go across.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}A teacher of the Law came up to him, and said, \uc1\u8220*Teacher, I will follow you wherever you go.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}\uc1\u8220*Foxes have holes,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8220*and wild birds their nests, but the Son of Man has nowhere to lay his head.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8220*Master,\uc1\u8221* said another, who was a disciple, \uc1\u8220*let me first go and bury my father.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}But Jesus answered, \uc1\u8220*Follow me, and leave the dead to bury their dead.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Then he got into the boat, followed by his disciples.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Suddenly so great a storm came up on the sea, that the waves broke right over the boat. But Jesus was asleep;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}and the disciples came and roused him. \uc1\u8220*Master,\uc1\u8221* they cried, \uc1\u8220*save us; we are lost!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}\uc1\u8220*Why are you so timid?\uc1\u8221* he said. \uc1\u8220*You of little faith!\uc1\u8221* Then Jesus rose and rebuked the winds and the sea, and a great calm followed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}The men were amazed, and exclaimed, \uc1\u8220*What kind of man is this, that even the winds and the sea obey him!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}On getting to the other side \uc1\u8211* the region of the Gadarenes \uc1\u8211* Jesus met two men who were possessed by demons, coming out of the tombs. They were so violent that no one was able to pass that way.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Suddenly they shrieked out, \uc1\u8220*What do you want with us, Son of God? Have you come here to torment us before our time?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}A long way off, there was a herd of many pigs, feeding;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}and the foul spirits began begging Jesus, \uc1\u8220*If you drive us out, send us into the herd of pigs.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}\uc1\u8220*Go,\uc1\u8221* he said. The spirits came out, and entered the pigs; and the whole herd rushed down the steep slope into the sea, and died in the water.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}At this the men who tended them ran away and went to the town, carrying the news of all that had occurred, and of what had happened to the possessed men.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}At the news the whole town went out to meet Jesus, and, when they saw him, they entreated him to go away from their region.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 9}Afterward Jesus got into a boat, and, crossing over, came to his own city.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}There some people brought to him a paralyzed man on a bed. When Jesus saw their faith, he said to the man, \uc1\u8220*Courage, child! Your sins are forgiven.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Then some of the teachers of the Law said to themselves, \uc1\u8220*This man is blaspheming!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Knowing their thoughts, Jesus exclaimed, \uc1\u8220*Why do your cherish such wicked thoughts?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Which, I ask, is the easier? \uc1\u8211* to say \uc1\u8216*Your sins are forgiven\uc1\u8217*? Or to say \uc1\u8216*Get up, and walk\uc1\u8217*?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But to show you that the Son of Man has power on earth to forgive sins\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211* then he said to the paralyzed man \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Get up, take up your bed, and return to your home.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The man got up and went to his home.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}When the crowd saw this, they were awe-struck, and praised God for giving such power to human beings.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}As Jesus went along, he saw a man, called Matthew, sitting in the tax office, and said to him, \uc1\u8220*Follow me.\uc1\u8221* Matthew got up and followed him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And, later on, when he was having dinner in the house, a number of tax collectors and outcasts came in and took their places at the table with Jesus and his disciples.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}When the Pharisees saw this, they said to his disciples, \uc1\u8220*Why does your teacher eat in the company of tax collectors and outcasts?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}On hearing this, Jesus said, \uc1\u8220*It is not those who are healthy who need a doctor, but those who are ill.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Go and learn what this means \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*I desire mercy, and not sacrifice\uc1\u8217*; for I did not come to call the religious, but the outcast.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Then John\uc1\u8217*s disciples came to Jesus, and asked, \uc1\u8220*Why do we and the Pharisees fast while your disciples do not?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Jesus answered, \uc1\u8220*Can the groom\uc1\u8217*s friends mourn as long as the groom is with them? But the days will come, when the groom will be taken away from them, and they will fast then.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Nobody ever puts a piece of unshrunk cloth on an old garment; for such a patch tears away from the garment, and a worse tear is made.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Nor do people put new wine into old wine-skins; for, if they do, the skins burst, and the wine runs out, and the skins are lost; but they put new wine into fresh skins, and so both are preserved.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}While Jesus was saying this, a synagogue leader came up and bowed to the ground before him. \uc1\u8220*My daughter,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*has just died; but come and place your hand on her, and she will be restored to life.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}So Jesus rose and followed him, and his disciples went also.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}But meanwhile a woman, who had been suffering from hemorrhage for twelve years, came up behind and touched the tassel of his cloak.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8220*If I only touch his cloak,\uc1\u8221* she said to herself, \uc1\u8220*I will get well.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Turning and seeing her, Jesus said, \uc1\u8220*Courage, daughter! Your faith has delivered you.\uc1\u8221* And at that very moment she became well.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}When Jesus reached the leader\uc1\u8217*s house, seeing the flute players, and a number of people all in confusion,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}he said, \uc1\u8220*Go away, the little girl is not dead; she is asleep.\uc1\u8221* They began to laugh at him;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}but, when the people had been sent out, Jesus went in, and took the little girl\uc1\u8217*s hand, and she rose.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}The report of this spread through all that part of the country.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}As Jesus was passing on from there, he was followed by two blind men, who kept calling out, \uc1\u8220*Take pity on us, Son of David!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}When he had gone indoors, the blind men came up to him; and Jesus asked them, \uc1\u8220*Do you believe that I am able to do this?\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8220*Yes, Master!\uc1\u8221* they answered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Then he touched their eyes, and said, \uc1\u8220*It will be according to your faith.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Then their eyes were opened. Jesus sternly cautioned them. \uc1\u8220*See that no one knows of it,\uc1\u8221* he said.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}But the men went out, and spread the news about him through all that part of the country.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Just as they were going out, some people brought up to Jesus a dumb man who was possessed by a demon;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}and, as soon as the demon had been driven out, the dumb man spoke. The people were astonished at this, and exclaimed, \uc1\u8220*Nothing like this has ever been seen in Israel!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}But the Pharisees said, \uc1\u8220*He drives out the demons by the help of the chief of the demons.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Jesus went around all the towns and the villages, teaching in their synagogues, proclaiming the good news of the kingdom, and curing every kind of disease and every kind of sickness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}But, when he saw the crowds, his heart was moved with compassion for them, because they were distressed and harassed, like sheep without a shepherd;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}and he said to his disciples, \uc1\u8220*The harvest is abundant, but the laborers are few.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}Therefore pray to the owner of the harvest to send laborers to gather in his harvest.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 10}Calling his twelve Disciples to him, Jesus gave them authority over foul spirits, so that they could drive them out, as well as the power of curing every kind of disease and every kind of sickness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The names of the twelve apostles are these, First Simon, also known as Peter, and his brother Andrew; James the son of Zebedee, and his brother John;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Philip and Bartholomew; Thomas and Matthew the tax-gather; James the son of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Simon the Zealot, and Judas Iscariot \uc1\u8211* the apostle who betrayed him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}These twelve Jesus sent out as his messengers, after giving them these instructions \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Do not go to the Gentiles, nor enter any Samaritan town,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}but make your way rather to the lost sheep of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}On your way proclaim that the kingdom of heaven is at hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Cure the sick, raise the dead, make the lepers clean, drive out demons. You have received free of cost, give free of cost.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Do not provide yourselves with gold, or silver, or coins in your purses;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}not even with a bag for the journey, or a change of clothes, or sandals, or even a staff; for the worker is worth his food.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Whatever town or village you visit, find out who is worthy in that place, and remain there until you leave.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}As you enter the house, greet it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then, if the house is worthy, let your blessing rest on it, but, if it is unworthy, let your blessing return on yourselves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}If no one welcomes you, or listens to what you say, as you leave that house or that town, shake off its dust from your feet.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}I tell you, the doom of the land of Sodom and Gomorrah will be more bearable in the day of judgment than the doom of that town.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8220*Remember, I am sending you out as my messengers like sheep among wolves. So be as wise as snakes, and as blameless as doves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Be on your guard against others, for they will betray you to courts of law, and scourge you in their synagogues;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}and you will be brought before governors and kings for my sake so that you may witness for me before them and the nations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Whenever they betray you, do not be anxious as to how you will speak or what you will say, for what you will say will be given you at the moment;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}for it will not be you who speak, but the Spirit of your Father that speaks within you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Brother will betray brother to death, and the father his child; and children will turn against their parents, and cause them to be put to death;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}and you will be hated by everyone because of me. Yet the person who endures to the end will be saved.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}But, when they persecute you in one town, escape to the next; for, I tell you, you will not have come to the end of the towns of Israel before the Son of Man comes.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}A student is not above his teacher, nor a servant above his master.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}It is enough for a student to be treated like his teacher, and a servant like his master. If the head of the house has been called Beelzebul, how much more the members of his household!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Do not, therefore, be afraid of them. There is nothing concealed which will not be revealed, nor anything hidden which will not become known.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}What I tell you in the dark, say again in the light; and what is whispered in your ear, proclaim on the housetops.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Do not be afraid of those who kill the body, but are unable to kill the soul; rather be afraid of him who is able to destroy both soul and body in Gehenna.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Are not two sparrows sold for a one copper coin? Yet not one of them will fall to the ground without your Father\uc1\u8217*s knowledge.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}While as for you, even the hairs of your head are numbered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Do not, therefore, be afraid; you are of more value than many sparrows.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Everyone, therefore, who will publicly acknowledge me, I, too, will acknowledge before my Father who is in heaven;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}but, if anyone publicly disowns me, I, too, will disown him before my Father who is in heaven.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}\uc1\u8220*Do not imagine that I have come to bring peace to the earth. I have come to bring, not peace, but the sword.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}For I have come to set a man against his father, and a daughter against her mother, and a daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}A person\uc1\u8217*s enemies will be the members of their own household.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Anyone who loves father or mother more than me is not worthy of me; and anyone who loves son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}Anyone who does not take their cross and follow in my steps is not worthy of me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}The person who has found their life will lose it, while the person who, for my sake, has lost their life will find it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}\uc1\u8220*Anyone who welcomes you is welcoming me; and anyone who welcomes me is welcoming him who sent me as his messenger.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}The person who welcomes a prophet, because they are a prophet, will receive a prophet\uc1\u8217*s reward; and anyone who welcomes a good person, because they are a good person, will receive a good person\uc1\u8217*s reward.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}And, if anyone gives but a cup of cold water to one of these little ones because they are a disciple, I tell you that they will assuredly not lose their reward.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 11}After Jesus had finished giving directions to his twelve Disciples, he left that place in order to teach and preach in their towns.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Now John had heard in prison what the Christ was doing, and he sent a message by his disciples,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and asked \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Are you \uc1\u8216*the coming one,\uc1\u8217* or are we to look for someone else?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}The answer of Jesus to the question was \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Go and report to John what you hear and see \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}the blind recover their sight and the lame walk, the lepers are made clean and the deaf hear, the dead, too, are raised to life, and the good news is told to the poor.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Blessed is the person who finds no hindrance in me.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}While John\uc1\u8217*s disciples were going back, Jesus began to say to the crowds with reference to John,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8220*What did you go out into the wilderness to look at? A reed waving in the wind? If not, what did you go out to see? A man richly dressed? Why, those who wear rich things are to be found in the courts of kings!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}What, then, did you go for? To see a prophet? Yes, I tell you, and far more than a prophet.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}This is the man of whom scripture says \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*I am sending my messenger ahead of you, and he will prepare your way before you.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}I tell you, no one born of a woman has yet appeared who is greater than John the Baptist; and yet the least in the kingdom of heaven is greater than he.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}From the time of John the Baptist to this very hour, the kingdom of heaven has been taken by force, and people using force have been seizing it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}For the teaching of all the prophets and of the Law continued until the time of John;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}and \uc1\u8211* if you are ready to accept it \uc1\u8211* John is himself the Elijah who was destined to come.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}If you have ears, listen.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}But to what will I compare the present generation? It is like little children sitting in the market-places and calling out to their playmates \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}We have played the flute for you, but you have not danced; We have wailed, but you have not mourned.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}For, when John came, neither eating nor drinking, people said \uc1\u8216*He has a demon in him\uc1\u8217*;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}and now that the Son of Man has come, eating and drinking, they are saying \uc1\u8216*Here is a glutton and a wine-drinker, a friend of tax collectors and outcasts!\uc1\u8217* And yet wisdom is vindicated by her actions.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Then Jesus began to reproach the towns in which most of his miracles had been done, because they had not repented,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8220*Alas for you, Chorazin! Alas for you, Bethsaida! For, if the miracles which were done in you had been done in Tyre and Sidon, they would have repented long ago in sackcloth and ashes.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Yet, I tell you, the doom of Tyre and Sidon will be more bearable in the day of judgment than yours.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And you, Capernaum! Will you exalt yourself to heaven? You will be flung down to Hades! For, if the miracles which have been done in you had been done in Sodom, it would have been standing to this day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Yet, I tell you, the doom of Sodom will be more bearable in the day of judgment than yours.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}At that same time Jesus uttered the words, \uc1\u8220*I thank you, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, that, though you have hidden these things from the wise and learned, you have revealed them to the childlike!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Yes, Father, I thank you that this has seemed good to you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Everything has been committed to me by my Father; nor does anyone fully know the Son, except the Father, or fully know the Father, except the Son and those to whom the Son may choose to reveal him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Come to me, all you who toil and are burdened, and I will give you rest!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Take my yoke on you, and learn from me, for I am gentle and humble, and you will find rest for your souls;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}for my yoke is easy, and my burden is light.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 12}About the same time Jesus walked through the cornfields one Sabbath. His disciples were hungry, and began to pick some ears of wheat and eat them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}But, when the Pharisees saw this, they said, \uc1\u8220*Look! Your disciples are doing what it is not allowable to do on a Sabbath!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}\uc1\u8220*Haven\uc1\u8217*t you read,\uc1\u8221* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8220*what David did, when he and his companions were hungry \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}how he went into the house of God, and how they ate the consecrated bread, through it was not allowable for him or his companions to eat it, but only for the priests?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And haven\uc1\u8217*t you read in the law that, on the Sabbath, the priest in the Temple break the Sabbath and yet are not guilty?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Here, however, I tell you, there is something greater than the Temple!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Had you learned the meaning of the words \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*I desire mercy, and not sacrifice,\uc1\u8217* you would not have condemned those who are not guilty.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}For the Son of Man is lord of the Sabbath.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Passing on, Jesus went into their synagogue,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}and there he saw a man with a withered hand. Some people asked Jesus whether it was allowable to work a cure on the Sabbath \uc1\u8211* so that they might have a charge to bring against him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But Jesus said to them, \uc1\u8220*Which of you, if he had only one sheep, and that sheep fell into a pit on the Sabbath, would not lay hold of it and pull it out?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}How much more precious a person is than a sheep! Therefore it is allowable to do good on the Sabbath.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then he said to the man. \uc1\u8220*Stretch out your hand.\uc1\u8221* The man stretched it out; and it had become as sound as the other.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}On coming out, the Pharisees plotted against Jesus, to put him to death.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Jesus, however, became aware of it, and went away from that place. A number of people followed him, and he cured them all;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}but he warned them not to make him known,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}in fulfillment of these words in the prophet Isaiah \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8216*Here is my chosen servant, who I love and who pleases me! I will breathe my spirit on him, and he will announce a time of judgment to the Gentiles.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}He will not contend, nor cry aloud, Neither will anyone hear his voice in the streets;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}a bruised reed he will not break, and a smoldering wick he will not quench, until he has brought the judgment to a victorious issue,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}and on his name will the Gentiles rest their hopes.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Then some people brought to Jesus a possessed man, who was blind and dumb; and he cured him, so that the man who had been dumb both talked and saw.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}At this all the people were astounded. \uc1\u8220*Is it possible that this is the son of David?\uc1\u8221* they exclaimed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}But the Pharisees heard of it and said, \uc1\u8220*He drives out demons only by the help of Beelzebul the chief of the demons.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Jesus, however, was aware of what was passing in their minds, and said to them, \uc1\u8220*Any kingdom divided against itself becomes a desolation, and any town or household divided against itself will not last.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}So, if Satan drives Satan out, he must be divided against himself; and how, then, can his kingdom last?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}And, if it is by Beelzebul\uc1\u8217*s help that I drive out demons, by whose help is it that your own sons drive them out? Therefore they will themselves be your judges.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}But, if it is by the help of the Spirit of God that I drive out demons, then the kingdom of God must already be upon you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}How, again, can anyone get into a strong man\uc1\u8217*s house and carry off his goods, without first securing him? Not until then will he plunder his house.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Anyone who is not with me is against me, and the person who does not help me to gather is scattering.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Therefore, I tell you, people will be forgiven every sin and slander; but slander against the Holy Spirit will not be forgiven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Whoever speaks against the Son of Man will be forgiven, but whoever speaks against the Holy Spirit will not be forgiven, either in the present age, or in the age to come.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}\uc1\u8220*You must assume either that both tree and fruit are good, or that both tree and fruit are worthless; since it is by its fruits that a tree is known.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}You children of snakes! How can you, evil as you are, say anything good? For what fills the heart will rise to the lips.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}A good person, from his good stores, produces good things; while an evil person, from his evil stores, produces evil things.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}I tell you that for every careless thing that people say, they must answer on the \uc1\u8216*day of judgment.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}For it is by your words that you will be acquitted, and by your words that you will be condemned.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}At this point, some teachers of the Law and Pharisees spoke up. \uc1\u8220*Teacher,\uc1\u8221* they said, \uc1\u8220*we want to see some sign from you.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}\uc1\u8220*It is a wicked and unfaithful generation,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8220*that is asking for a sign, and no sign will be given it except the sign of the prophet Jonah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}For, just as Jonah was inside the sea-monster three days and three nights, so will the Son of Man be three days and three nights in the heart of the earth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}At the judgment, the people of Nineveh will stand up with this generation, and will condemn it, because they repented at Jonah\uc1\u8217*s proclamation; and here is more than a Jonah!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}At the judgment the Queen of the South will rise up with the present generation, and will condemn it, because she came from the ends of the earth to listen to the wisdom of Solomon; and here is more than a Solomon!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}No sooner does a foul spirit leave a person, than it passes through places where there is no water, in search of rest, and does not find it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}Then it says \uc1\u8216*I will go back to the home which I left\uc1\u8217*; but, on coming there, it finds it unoccupied, and swept, and put in order.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}Then it goes and brings with it seven other spirits more wicked than itself, and they go in, and make their home there; and the last state of that man proves to be worse than the first. So, too, will it be with this wicked generation.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}While he was still speaking to the crowds, his mother and brothers were standing outside, asking to speak to him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}Someone told him this, and Jesus replied,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}\uc1\u8220*Who is my mother? And who are my brothers?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}Then, stretching out his hands towards his disciples, he said, \uc1\u8220*Here are my mother and my brothers!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}For anyone who does the will of my Father who is in heaven is my brother and sister and mother.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 13}That same day, when Jesus had left the house and was sitting by the sea,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}such great crowds gathered around him, that he got into a boat, and sat in it, while all the people stood on the beach.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Then he told them many truths in parables. \uc1\u8220*The sower,\uc1\u8221* he began, \uc1\u8220*went out to sow; and,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}as they were sowing, some seed fell along the path, and the birds came and ate it up.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Some fell on rocky places, where it had not much soil, and, because the soil wasn\uc1\u8217*t deep, sprang up at once.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}As soon as the sun had risen, it was scorched, and, because their roots were not deep enough, withered away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Some, again, fell into the brambles; but the brambles shot up and choked it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Some, however, fell on good soil, and yielded a return, sometimes one hundred, sometimes sixty, sometimes thirty fold.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Let those who have ears hear.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Afterward his disciples came to him, and said, \uc1\u8220*Why do you speak to them in parables?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8220*To you,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8220*the knowledge of the hidden truths of the kingdom of heaven has been imparted, but not to those.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}For, to all who have, more will be given, and they will have abundance; but, from all who have nothing, even what they have will be taken away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}That is why I speak to them in parables, because, though they have eyes, they do not see, and though they have ears, they do not hear or understand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}In them is being fulfilled that prophecy of Isaiah which says \uc1\u8211*
