{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8220*Listen, then, yourselves to the parable of the sower.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}When anyone hears the message of the kingdom without understanding it, the evil one comes and snatches away what has been sown in their mind. This is the person meant by the seed which was sown along the path.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}By the seed which was sown on rocky places is meant the person who hears the message, and at once accepts it joyfully;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}but, as they have no root, they stand for only a short time; and, when trouble or persecution arises because of the message, they fall away at once.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}By the seed which was sown among the brambles is meant the person who hears the message, but the cares of life and the glamour of wealth completely choke the message, so that it gives no return.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}But by the seed which was sown on the good ground is meant the person who hears the message and understands it, and really yields a return, sometimes one hundred, sometimes sixty, sometimes thirty fold.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Another parable which Jesus told them was this \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*The kingdom of heaven is compared to a person who sowed good seed in their field.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}But, while everyone was asleep, their enemy came and sowed weeds among the wheat, and then went away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}So, when the blades of corn shot up, and came into ear, the weeds made their appearance also.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}The owner\uc1\u8217*s servants came to them, and said \uc1\u8216*Was not it good seed that you sowed in your field? Where, then, do the weeds in it come from?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}\uc1\u8216*An enemy has done this,\uc1\u8217* was the owner\uc1\u8217*s answer. \uc1\u8216*Do you wish us, then,\uc1\u8217* they asked, \uc1\u8216*to go and gather them together?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}\uc1\u8216*No,\uc1\u8217* said he, \uc1\u8216*because while you are pulling up the weeds you might uproot the wheat with them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Let both grow side by side until harvest; and then I will say to the reapers, Gather the weeds together first, and tie them in bundles for burning; but bring all the wheat into my barn.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Another parable which he told them was this \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*The kingdom of heaven is like a mustard seed, which a person took and sowed in his field.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}This seed is smaller than all other seeds, but, when it has grown up, it is larger than the herbs and becomes a tree, so that \uc1\u8216*the wild birds come and roost in its branches.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}This was another parable which Jesus related \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*The kingdom of heaven is like some yeast which a woman took and covered up in three pecks of flour, until the whole had risen.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Of all this Jesus spoke to the crowd in parables; indeed to them he used never to speak at all except in parables,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}in fulfillment of these words in the prophet \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*I will speak to them in parables; I will utter things kept secret since the foundation of the world.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Then Jesus left the crowd, and went into the house. Presently his disciples came to him, and said, \uc1\u8220*Explain to us the parable of the weeds in the field.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}He answered, \uc1\u8220*The sower of the good seed is the Son of Man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}The field is the world. By the good seed is meant the people of the kingdom. The weeds are the wicked,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}and the enemy who sowed them is the devil. The harvest time is the close of the age, and the reapers are angels.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}And, just as the weeds are gathered and burnt, so it will be at the close of the age.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}The Son of Man will send his angels, and they will gather from his kingdom all that hinders and those who live in sin,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}and will throw them into the blazing furnace, where there will be weeping and grinding of teeth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}Then will the righteous shine, like the sun, in the kingdom of their Father. If you have ears, listen.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}\uc1\u8220*The kingdom of heaven is like a treasure hidden in a field, which a person found and hid again, and then, in their delight, went and sold everything that they had, and bought that field.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}\uc1\u8220*Again, the kingdom of heaven is like a merchant in search of choice pearls.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}Finding one of great value, they went and sold everything that they had, and bought it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}Or again, the kingdom of heaven is like a net which was cast into the sea, and caught fish of all kinds.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}When it was full, they hauled it up on the beach, and sat down and sorted the good fish into baskets, but threw the worthless ones away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}So will it be at the close of the age. The angels will go out and separate the wicked from the righteous,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}and will throw them into the blazing furnace, where there will be weeping and grinding of teeth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}\uc1\u8220*Have you understood all this?\uc1\u8221* Jesus asked. \uc1\u8220*Yes,\uc1\u8221* they answered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}Then he added, \uc1\u8220*So every teacher of the Law, who has received instruction about the kingdom of heaven, is like a householder who produces from his stores things both new and old.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}When Jesus had finished these parables, he withdrew from that place.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}Going to his own part of the country, he taught the people in their synagogue in such a manner that they were deeply impressed. \uc1\u8220*Where did he get this wisdom?\uc1\u8221* they said, \uc1\u8220*and the miracles?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}Isn\uc1\u8217*t he the carpenter\uc1\u8217*s son? Isn\uc1\u8217*t his mother called Mary, and his brothers James, and Joseph, and Simon, and Judas?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}And his sisters, too \uc1\u8211* are not they all living among us? Where, then did he get all this?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 57}These things proved a hindrance to their believing in him. But Jesus said, \uc1\u8220*A prophet is not without honor, except in his own country and in his own house.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 58}He did not work many miracles there, because of their want of faith.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 14}At that time Prince Herod heard of the fame of Jesus,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and said to his attendants, \uc1\u8220*This must be John the Baptist; he must be risen from the dead, and that is why these miraculous powers are active in him.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}For Herod had arrested John, put him in chains, and shut him up in prison, to please Herodias, the wife of Herod\uc1\u8217*s brother Philip.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For John had said to him \uc1\u8216*You have no right to be living with her.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Yet, though Herod wanted to put him to death, he was afraid of the people, because they looked on John as a prophet.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But, when Herod\uc1\u8217*s birthday came, the daughter of Herodias danced before his guests, and so pleased Herod,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}that he promised with an oath to give her whatever she asked.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Prompted by her mother, the girl said \uc1\u8216*Give me here, on a dish, the head of John the Baptist.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The king was distressed at this; yet, because of his oath and of the guests at his table, he ordered it to be given her.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}He had John beheaded in the prison{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}and his head was brought on a dish and given to the girl, and she took it to her mother.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Then John\uc1\u8217*s disciples came, and took the body away, and buried it; and went and told Jesus.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}When Jesus heard of it, he left privately in a boat to a lonely spot. The people, however, heard of his going, and followed him in crowds from the towns on foot.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}On getting out of the boat, Jesus saw a great crowd, and his heart was moved at the sight of them; and he cured all the sick among them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}In the evening the disciples came up to him, and said, \uc1\u8220*This is a lonely spot, and the day is now far advanced; send the crowds away so that they can go to the villages, and buy themselves food.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}But Jesus said, \uc1\u8220*They need not go away, it is for you to give them something to eat.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8220*We have nothing here,\uc1\u8221* they said, \uc1\u8220*except five loaves and two fish.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8220*Bring them here to me,\uc1\u8221* was his reply.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Jesus ordered the people to take their seats on the grass; and, taking the five loaves and the two fish, he looked up to heaven, and said the blessing, and, after he had broken the loaves, gave them to his disciples; and they gave them to the crowds.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Everyone had sufficient to eat, and they picked up enough of the broken pieces that were left to fill twelve baskets.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}The men who ate were about five thousand in number, without counting women and children.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Immediately afterward Jesus made the disciples get into a boat and cross over in advance of him, while he dismissed the crowds.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}After dismissing the crowds, he went up the hill by himself to pray; and, when evening fell, he was there alone.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}The boat was by this time some miles from shore, laboring in the waves, for the wind was against her.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Three hours after midnight, however, Jesus came towards the disciples, walking on the water.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}But, when they saw him walking on the water, they were terrified. \uc1\u8220*It is a ghost,\uc1\u8221* they exclaimed, and cried out in fear.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}But Jesus at once spoke to them. \uc1\u8220*Courage!\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*It is I; do not be afraid!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}\uc1\u8220*Master,\uc1\u8221* Peter exclaimed, \uc1\u8220*if it is you, tell me to come to you on the water.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Jesus said, \uc1\u8220*Come.\uc1\u8221* So Peter got down from the boat, and walked on the water, and went towards Jesus;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}but, when he felt the wind, he was frightened, and, beginning to sink, cried out, \uc1\u8220*Master! Save me!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Instantly Jesus stretched out his hand, and caught hold of him. \uc1\u8220*You of little faith!\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*Why did you falter?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}When they had got into the boat, the wind dropped.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}But the men in the boat threw themselves on their faces before him, and said, \uc1\u8220*You are indeed God\uc1\u8217*s Son.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}When they had crossed over, they landed at Gennesaret.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}But the people of that place, recognizing Jesus, sent out to the whole country around, and brought to him all who were ill,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}begging him merely to let them touch the tassel of his cloak; and all who touched were made perfectly well.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 15}Then some Pharisees and teachers of the Law came to Jesus, and said,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8220*How is it that your disciples break the traditions of our ancestors? For they do not wash their hands when they eat food.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}His reply was, \uc1\u8220*How is it that you on your side break God\uc1\u8217*s commandments out of respect for your own traditions?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For God said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Honor your father and mother,\uc1\u8217* and \uc1\u8216*Anyone who abuses his father or mother shall suffer death,\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}but you say \uc1\u8216*Whenever anyone says to his father or mother \uc1\u8220*Whatever of mine might have been of service to you is set apart for God,\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}he is in no way bound to honor his father.\uc1\u8217* In this way you have nullified the words of God for the sake of your traditions.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Hypocrites! It was well said by Isaiah when he prophesied about you \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8216*This is a people that honor me with their lips, While their hearts are far removed from me;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}but vainly do they worship me, For they teach but human precepts.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Then Jesus called the people to him, and said, \uc1\u8220*Listen, and mark my words.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}It is not what enters a person\uc1\u8217*s mouth that defiles them, but what comes out from their mouth \uc1\u8211* that does defile them!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}His disciples came up to him, and said, \uc1\u8220*Do you know that the Pharisees were shocked on hearing what you said?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8220*Every plant,\uc1\u8221* Jesus replied, \uc1\u8220*that my heavenly Father has not planted will be rooted up.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Leave them be; they are but blind guides; and, if one blind person guides another, both of them will fall into a ditch.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Peter spoke up, \uc1\u8220*Explain this saying to us.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8220*What, do even you understand nothing yet?\uc1\u8221* Jesus exclaimed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8220*Don\uc1\u8217*t you see that whatever goes into the mouth passes into the stomach, and is afterward expelled?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}But the things that come out of the mouth proceed from the heart, and it is these that defile a person;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}for out of the heart proceed evil thoughts \uc1\u8211* murder, adultery, sexual immorality, theft, perjury, slander.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}These are the things that defile a person; but eating with unwashed hands does not defile a person.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}On going away from that place, Jesus went to the country around Tyre and Sidon.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}There, a Canaanite woman of that district came out and began calling to Jesus, \uc1\u8220*Take pity on me, Master, Son of David; my daughter is grievously possessed by a demon.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}But Jesus did not answer her a word; and his disciples came up and begged him to send her away. \uc1\u8220*She keeps calling out after us,\uc1\u8221* they said.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}\uc1\u8220*I was not sent,\uc1\u8221* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8220*to anyone except the lost sheep of Israel.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}But the woman came, and, bowing to the ground before him, said, \uc1\u8220*Master, help me.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}\uc1\u8220*It is not fair,\uc1\u8221* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8220*to take the children\uc1\u8217*s food and throw it to dogs.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}\uc1\u8220*Yes, Master,\uc1\u8221* she said, \uc1\u8220*for even dogs do feed on the scraps that fall from their owners\uc1\u8217* table.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}\uc1\u8220*Your faith is great,\uc1\u8221* was his reply to the woman, \uc1\u8220*it will be as you wish!\uc1\u8221* And her daughter was cured that very hour.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}On leaving that place, Jesus went to the shore of the Sea of Galilee; and then went up the hill, and sat down.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Great crowds of people came to him, bringing with them those who were lame, crippled, blind, or dumb, and many others. They put them down at his feet, and he cured them;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}and the crowds were astonished, when they saw the dumb talking, the cripples made sound, the lame walking about, and the blind with their sight restored; and they praised the God of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Afterward Jesus called his disciples to him, and said, \uc1\u8220*My heart is moved at the sight of all these people, for they have already been with me three days and they have nothing to eat; and I am unwilling to send them away hungry; they might faint on the way home.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}\uc1\u8220*Where can we,\uc1\u8221* his disciples asked, \uc1\u8220*in a lonely place find enough bread for such a crowd as this?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}\uc1\u8220*How many loaves have you?\uc1\u8221* said Jesus. \uc1\u8220*Seven,\uc1\u8221* they answered, \uc1\u8220*and a few small fish.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Telling the crowd to sit down on the ground,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Jesus took the seven loaves and the fish, and, after saying the thanksgiving, broke them, and gave them to the disciples; and the disciples gave them to the crowds.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Everyone had sufficient to eat, and they picked up seven baskets full of the broken pieces left.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}The men who ate were four thousand in number without counting women and children.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}Then, after dismissing the crowds, Jesus got into the boat, and went to the region of Magadan.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 16}Here the Pharisees and Sadducees came up, and, to test Jesus, requested him to show them some sign from the heavens.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}But Jesus answered, \uc1\u8220*In the evening you say \uc1\u8216*It will be fine weather, for the sky is as red as fire.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}But in the morning you say \uc1\u8216*Today it will be stormy, for the sky is as red as fire and threatening.\uc1\u8217* You learn to read the sky; yet you are unable to read the signs of the times!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}A wicked and unfaithful generation is asking for a sign, but no sign will be given it except the sign of Jonah.\uc1\u8221* So he left them and went away.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Now the disciples had crossed to the opposite shore, and had forgotten to take any bread.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Presently Jesus said to them, \uc1\u8220*Take care and be on your guard against the leaven of the Pharisees and Sadducees.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}But the disciples began talking among themselves about their having brought no bread.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}On noticing this, Jesus said, \uc1\u8220*Why are you talking among yourselves about your being short of bread, you of little faith?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Don\uc1\u8217*t you yet see, nor remember the five loaves for the five thousand, and how many baskets you took away?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Nor yet the seven loaves for the four thousand, and how many basketfuls you took away?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}How is it that you do not see that I was not speaking about bread? Be on your guard against the leaven of the Pharisees and Sadducees.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Then they understood that he had told them to be on their guard, not against the leaven of bread, but against the teaching of the Pharisees and Sadducees.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}On coming into the region of Caesarea Philippi, Jesus asked his disciples this question \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Who do people say that the Son of Man is?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}\uc1\u8220*Some say John the Baptist,\uc1\u8221* they answered, \uc1\u8220*Others, however, say that he is Elijah, while others again say Jeremiah, or one of the prophets.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}\uc1\u8220*But you,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*who do you say that I am?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}To this Simon Peter answered, \uc1\u8220*You are the Christ, the Son of the living God.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8220*Blessed are you, Simon, Son of Jonah,\uc1\u8221* Jesus replied. \uc1\u8220*For no human being has revealed this to you, but my Father who is in heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Yes, and I say to you, your name is \uc1\u8216*Peter\uc1\u8217* \uc1\u8211* a Rock, and on this rock I will build my church, and the gates of Hades will not prevail over it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}I will give you the keys of the kingdom of heaven. Whatever you forbid on earth will be held in heaven to be forbidden, and whatever you allow on earth will be held in heaven to be allowed.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Then he charged his disciples not to tell anyone that he was the Christ.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}At that time Jesus Christ began to explain to his disciples that he must go to Jerusalem, and undergo much suffering at the hands of the elders, and chief priests, and teachers of the Law, and be put to death, and rise on the third day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}But Peter took Jesus aside, and began to rebuke him. \uc1\u8220*Master,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*please God that will never be your fate!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Jesus, however, turning to Peter, said, \uc1\u8220*Out of my way, Satan! You are a hindrance to me; for you look at things, not as God does, but as person does.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Then Jesus said to his disciples, \uc1\u8220*If anyone wishes to walk in my steps, they must renounce self, and take up their cross, and follow me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}For whoever wishes to save his life will lose it, and whoever, for my sake, loses his life will find it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}What good will it do a person to gain the whole world, if he forfeits his life? Or what will a person give that is of equal value with his life?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}For the Son of Man is to come in his Father\uc1\u8217*s glory, with his angels, and then he will give to everyone what his actions deserve.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}I tell you, some of those who are standing here will not know death until they have seen the Son of Man coming into his kingdom.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 17}Six days later, Jesus took with him Peter, and the brothers James and John, and led them up a high mountain alone.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}There his appearance was transformed before their eyes; his face shown like the sun, and his clothes became as white as the light.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}All at once Moses and Elijah appeared to them, talking with Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}\uc1\u8220*Master,\uc1\u8221* exclaimed Peter, interposing, \uc1\u8220*it is good to be here; if you wish, I will make three tents here, one for you, one for Moses, and one for Elijah.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}While he was still speaking, a bright cloud enveloped them, and there was a voice from the cloud that said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*This is my dearly loved son, who brings me great joy; listen to him.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}The disciples, on hearing this, fell on their faces, greatly afraid.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}But Jesus came and touched them, saying as he did so, \uc1\u8220*Rise up, and do not be afraid.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}When they raised their eyes, they saw no one but Jesus himself alone.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}As they were going down the mountain side, Jesus gave them this warning \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Do not speak of this vision to anyone, until the Son of Man has risen from the dead.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8220*How is it,\uc1\u8221* his disciples asked, \uc1\u8220*that our teachers of the Law say that Elijah has to come first?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8220*Elijah indeed does come,\uc1\u8221* Jesus replied, \uc1\u8220*and will restore everything;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}and I tell you that Elijah has already come, and people have not recognized him, but have treated him just as they pleased. In the same way, too, the Son of Man is destined to undergo suffering at people\uc1\u8217*s hands.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then the disciples understood that he had spoken to them about John the Baptist.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}When they came to the crowd, a man came up to Jesus, and, kneeling down before him, said,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}\uc1\u8220*Master, take pity on my son, for he is epileptic and suffers terribly; indeed, he often falls into the fire and into the water;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}I brought him to your disciples, but they could not cure him.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8220*Faithless and perverse generation!\uc1\u8221* Jesus exclaimed, \uc1\u8220*how long must I be among you? How long must I have patience with you? Bring the boy here to me.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Then Jesus rebuked the demon, and it came out of the boy; and he was cured from that very hour.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Afterward the disciples came up to Jesus, and asked him privately, \uc1\u8220*Why was it that we could not drive it out?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}\uc1\u8220*Because you have so little faith!\uc1\u8221* he answered, \uc1\u8220*For, I tell you, if your faith were only like a mustard seed, you could say to this mountain \uc1\u8216*Move from this place to that!\uc1\u8217* and it would be moved; and nothing would be impossible to you.\uc1\u8221*{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}  Some later manuscripts add: But this kind does not go out except by prayer and fasting. }
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}While Jesus and his disciples were together in Galilee, he said to them, \uc1\u8220*The Son of Man is destined to be betrayed into human hands,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}and they will put him to death, but on the third day he will rise.\uc1\u8221* The disciples were greatly distressed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}After they had reached Capernaum, the collectors of the Temple taz came up to Peter, and said, \uc1\u8220*Does not your Master pay the Temple tax?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}\uc1\u8220*Yes,\uc1\u8221* answered Peter. But, on going into the house, before he could speak, Jesus said, \uc1\u8220*What do you think, Simon? From whom do earthly kings take taxes or tribute? From their sons, or from others?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}\uc1\u8220*From others,\uc1\u8221* answered Peter. \uc1\u8220*Well then,\uc1\u8221* continued Jesus, \uc1\u8220*their sons go free.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Still, so we don\uc1\u8217*t offend them, go and throw a line into the sea; take the first fish that rises, open its mouth, and you will find in it a piece of money. Take that, and give it to the collectors for both of us.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 18}On the same occasion the disciples came to Jesus, and asked him, \uc1\u8220*Who is really the greatest in the kingdom of heaven?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Jesus called a little child to him, and placed it in the middle of them, and then said,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}\uc1\u8220*I tell you, unless you change and become like little children, you will not enter the kingdom of heaven at all.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Therefore, anyone who will humble themselves like this child \uc1\u8211* that person will be the greatest in the kingdom of heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And anyone who, for the sake of my name, welcomes even one little child like this, is welcoming me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But, if anyone puts temptation in the way of one of these little ones who believe in me, it would be best for them to be sunk in the depths of the sea with a great millstone hung around their neck.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Alas for the world because of such temptations! There cannot but be temptations but sorrow awaits the person who does the tempting!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8220*If your hand or your foot causes you to sin, cut it off, and throw it away. It would be better for you to enter life maimed or lame, than to have both hands, or both feet, and be thrown into the fire that never goes out.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}If your eye causes you to sin, take it out, and throw it away. It would be better for you to enter the life with only one eye, than to have both eyes and be thrown into the fires of Gehenna.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Beware of despising one of these little ones, for in heaven, I tell you, their angels always see the face of my Father who is in heaven.{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}   Some later manuscripts add: For the Son of Man has come to save the lost. }
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}\uc1\u8220*What think you? If a person owns a hundred sheep, and one of them strays, will the person not leave the ninety-nine on the hills, and go and search for the one that is straying?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And, if they succeed in finding it, I tell you that they rejoice more over that one sheep than over the ninety-nine which did not stray.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}So, too, it is the will of my Father who is in heaven that not one of these little ones should be lost.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}\uc1\u8220*If your brother or sister does wrong, go to them and convince them of their fault when you are both alone. If they listen to you, you have won them over.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}But, if they do not listen to you, take with you one or two others, so that on the evidence of two or three witnesses, every word may be put beyond dispute.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}If they refuse to listen to them, speak to the church; and, if they also refuse to listen to the church, treat him as you would a Gentile or a tax-gatherer.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8220*I tell you, all that you forbid on earth will be held in heaven to be forbidden, and all that you allow on earth will be held in heaven to be allowed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Again, I tell you that, if but two of you on earth agree as to what they will pray for, whatever it be, it will be granted them by my Father who is in heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}For where two or three have come together in my name, I am present with them.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Then Peter came up, and said to Jesus, \uc1\u8220*Master, how often am I to forgive someone who wrongs me? As many as seven times?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}But Jesus answered, \uc1\u8220*Not seven times, but seventy times seven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Therefore the kingdom of heaven may be compared to a king who wished to settle accounts with his servants.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}When he had begun to do so, one of them was brought to him who owed him ten thousand bags of gold;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}and, as he could not pay, his master ordered him to be sold towards the payment of the debt, together with his wife, and his children, and everything that he had.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}The servant threw himself down on the ground before him and said \uc1\u8216*Have patience with me, and I will pay you all.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}The master was moved with compassion; and he let him go, and forgave him the debt.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}But, on going out, that same servant came upon one of his fellow servants who owed him a hundred silver coins. Seizing him by the throat, he said \uc1\u8216*Pay what you owe me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}His fellow servant threw himself on the ground and begged for mercy. \uc1\u8216*Have patience with me,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*and I will pay you.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}But the other would not, but went and put him in prison until he should pay his debt.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}When his fellow servants saw what had happened, they were greatly distressed, and went to their master and laid the whole matter before him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}So the master sent for the servant, and said to him \uc1\u8216*You wicked servant! When you begged me for mercy, I forgave you the whole of that debt.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}Shouldn\uc1\u8217*t you, also, to have shown mercy to your fellow servant, just as I showed mercy to you?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Then his master, in anger, handed him over to the jailers, until he should pay the whole of his debt.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}So, also, will my heavenly Father do to you, unless each one of you forgives his brother or sister from your heart.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Journey to Jerusalem

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 19}At the conclusion of this teaching, Jesus withdrew from Galilee, and went into that district of Judea which is on the other side of the Jordan.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Great crowds followed him, and he cured them there.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Presently some Pharisees came up to him, and, to test him, said, \uc1\u8220*Has a man the right to divorce his wife for every cause?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}\uc1\u8220*Haven\uc1\u8217*t you read,\uc1\u8221* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8220*that at the beginning the Creator \uc1\u8216*made them male and female,\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}and said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*For this reason a man will leave his father and mother, and be united to his wife, and the man and his wife will become one\uc1\u8217*?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}So that they are no longer two, but one. What God himself, then, has yoked together people must not separate.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}\uc1\u8220*Why, then,\uc1\u8221* they said, \uc1\u8220*did Moses direct that a man should serve his wife with a notice of separation and divorce her?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8220*Moses, owing to the hardness of your hearts,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8220*permitted you to divorce your wives, but that was not so at the beginning.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}But I tell you that anyone who divorces his wife, except on the ground of some serious sexual sin, and marries another woman, is guilty of adultery.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8220*If that,\uc1\u8221* said the disciples, \uc1\u8220*is the position of a man with regard to his wife, it is better not to marry.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8220*It is not everyone,\uc1\u8221* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8220*who can accept this teaching, but only those who have been enabled to do so.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Some men are incapable of marriage because they were born that way, or have been made so by other people, while there are others who stay single for the sake of the kingdom of Heaven. Accept this if you can.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then some little children were brought to Jesus, for him to place his hands on them, and pray; but the disciples found fault with those who had brought them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Jesus, however, said, \uc1\u8220*Let the little children come to me, and do not hinder them, for it is to the childlike that the kingdom of heaven belongs.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}So he placed his hands on them, and then went on his way.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}A man came up to Jesus, and said, \uc1\u8220*Teacher, what good thing must I do to obtain eternal life?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8220*Why ask me about goodness?\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus. \uc1\u8220*There is but One who is good. If you want to enter the life, keep the commandments.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8220*What commandments?\uc1\u8221* asked the man. \uc1\u8220*These,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*\uc1\u8216*You must not kill. You must not commit adultery. You must not steal. You must not say what is false about others.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Honor your father and your mother.\uc1\u8217* And \uc1\u8216*You must love your neighbor as you love yourself.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}\uc1\u8220*I have observed all these,\uc1\u8221* said the young man. \uc1\u8220*What is still wanting in me?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8220*If you wish to be perfect,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8220*go and sell your property, and give to the poor, and you will have wealth in heaven; then come and follow me.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}On hearing these words, the young man went away distressed, for he had great possessions.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}At this, Jesus said to his disciples, \uc1\u8220*I tell you that a rich person will find it hard to enter the kingdom of heaven!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}I say again, it is easier for a camel to get through a needle\uc1\u8217*s eye than for a rich person to enter the kingdom of heaven!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}On hearing this, the disciples exclaimed in great astonishment, \uc1\u8220*Who then can possibly be saved?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}But Jesus looked at them, and said, \uc1\u8220*With people this is impossible, but with God everything is possible.\uc1\u8221* Then Peter turned and said to Jesus,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}\uc1\u8220*But we \uc1\u8211* we left everything, and followed you; what, then, will we have?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}\uc1\u8220*I tell you,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8220*that at the new creation, when the Son of Man takes his seat on his throne of glory, you who followed me will be seated on twelve thrones, as judges of the twelve tribes of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Everyone who has left houses, or brothers, or sisters, or father, or mother, or children, or land, for my sake, will receive many times as much, and will gain eternal life.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}But many who are first now will then be last, and those who are last will be first.{\cf1\f1\fs22 20}For the kingdom of heaven is like an employer who went out in the early morning to hire laborers for his vineyards.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}He agreed with the laborers to pay them the standard daily rate of two silver coins, and sent them into his vineyard.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}On going out again, about nine o\uc1\u8217*clock, he saw some others standing in the marketplace, doing nothing.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}\uc1\u8216*You also may go into my vineyard,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*and I will pay you what is fair.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}So they went. Going out again about midday and about three o\uc1\u8217*clock, he did as before.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}When he went out about five, he found some others standing there, and said to them \uc1\u8216*Why have you been standing here all day long, doing nothing?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}\uc1\u8216*Because no one has hired us,\uc1\u8217* they answered. \uc1\u8216*You also may go into my vineyard,\uc1\u8217* he said.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}In the evening the owner of the vineyard said to his steward \uc1\u8216*Call the laborers, and pay them their wages, beginning with the last, and ending with the first.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Now when those who had been hired about five o\uc1\u8217*clock went up, they received two silver coins each.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}So, when the first went up, they thought that they would receive more, but they also received two silver coins each;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}at which they began to grumble at their employer.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}\uc1\u8216*These last,\uc1\u8217* they said, \uc1\u8216*have done only one hour\uc1\u8217*s work, and yet you have put them on the same footing with us, who have borne the brunt of the day\uc1\u8217*s work, and the heat.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8216*My friend,\uc1\u8217* was his reply to one of them, \uc1\u8216*I am not treating you unfairly. Didn\uc1\u8217*t you agree with me for two silver coins?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Take what belongs to you, and go. I choose to give to this last man the same as to you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Don\uc1\u8217*t I have the right to do as I choose with what is mine? Are you envious because I am generous?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}So those who are last will be first, and the first last.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}When Jesus was on the point of going up to Jerusalem, he gathered the twelve disciples around him by themselves, and said to them as they were on their way,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8220*Listen! We are going up to Jerusalem; and there the Son of Man will be betrayed to the chief priests and teachers of the Law, and they will condemn him to death,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}and give him up to the Gentiles for them to mock, and to scourge, and to crucify; and on the third day he will rise.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Then the mother of Zebedee\uc1\u8217*s sons came to him with her sons, bowing to the ground, and begging a favor.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8220*What is it that you want?\uc1\u8221* he asked. \uc1\u8220*I want you to say,\uc1\u8221* she replied, \uc1\u8220*that in your kingdom these two sons of mine may sit, one on your right, and the other on your left.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}\uc1\u8220*You do not know what you are asking,\uc1\u8221* was Jesus\uc1\u8217* answer. \uc1\u8220*Can you drink the cup that I am to drink?\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8220*Yes,\uc1\u8221* they exclaimed, \uc1\u8220*we can.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8220*You will indeed drink my cup,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*but as to a seat at my right and at my left \uc1\u8211* that is not mine to give, but it is for those for whom it has been prepared by my Father.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}On hearing of this, the ten others were very indignant about the two brothers.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Jesus, however, called the ten to him, and said, \uc1\u8220*The rulers of the Gentiles lord it over them as you know, and their high officials oppress them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Among you it is not so.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}No, whoever wants to become great among you must be your servant, and whoever wants to take the first place among you, must be your slave;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}just as the Son of Man came, not to be served, but to serve, and to give his life as a ransom for many.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}As they were going out of Jericho, a great crowd followed him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Two blind men who were sitting by the roadside, hearing that Jesus was passing, called out, \uc1\u8220*Take pity on us, Master, Son of David!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}The crowd told them to be quiet; but the men only called out the louder, \uc1\u8220*Take pity on us, Master, Son of David!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Then Jesus stopped and called them. \uc1\u8220*What do you want me to do for you?\uc1\u8221* he said.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}\uc1\u8220*Master,\uc1\u8221* they replied, \uc1\u8220*we want our eyes to be opened.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}So Jesus, moved with compassion, touched their eyes, and immediately they recovered their sight, and followed him.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Last Days

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 21}When they had almost reached Jerusalem, having come as far as Bethphage, on the Mount of Olives, Jesus sent on two disciples.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8220*Go to the village facing you,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*and you will immediately find a donkey tethered, with a foal by her side; untie her, and lead her here for me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And, if anyone says anything to you, you are to say this \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*The Master wants them\uc1\u8217*; and he will send them at once.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}This happened in fulfillment of these words in the prophet \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8216*Say to the people of Zion \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Your King is coming to you, gentle, and riding on a donkey, and on the foal of a beast of burden.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}So the disciples went and did as Jesus had directed them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}They led the donkey and the foal back, and, when they had put their cloaks on them, he seated himself on them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The immense crowd of people spread their cloaks in the road, while some cut branches off the trees, and spread them on the road.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The crowds that led the way, as well as those that followed behind, kept shouting, \uc1\u8220*God save the Son of David! Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord! God save him from on high!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}When he had entered Jerusalem, the whole city was stirred, and asked \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8220*Who is this?\uc1\u8221*, to which the crowd replied \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*This is the prophet Jesus from Nazareth in Galilee.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Jesus went into the Temple Courts, and drove out all those who were buying and selling there. He overturned the tables of the money changers, and the seats of the pigeon-dealers,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}and said to them, \uc1\u8220*Scripture says \uc1\u8216*My house will be called a house of prayer\uc1\u8217*; but you are making it a den of robbers.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}While he was still in the Temple Courts, some blind and some lame people came up to him, and he cured them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}But, when the chief priests and the teachers of the Law saw the wonderful things that Jesus did, and the boys who were calling out in the Temple Courts \uc1\u8220*God save the Son of David!\uc1\u8221*, they were indignant,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}and said to him, \uc1\u8220*Do you hear what these boys are saying?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 \uc1\u8220*Yes,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8220*but did you never read the words \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Out of the mouths of babes and sucklings you have called forth perfect praise\uc1\u8217*?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Then he left them, and went out of the city to Bethany, and spent the night there.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}The next morning, in returning to the city, Jesus became hungry;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}and, noticing a solitary fig tree by the roadside, he went up to it, but found nothing on it but leaves. So he said to it, \uc1\u8220*Never again will fruit be gathered off you.\uc1\u8221* And suddenly the fruit tree withered up.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}When the disciples saw this, they exclaimed in astonishment, \uc1\u8220*How suddenly the fig tree withered up!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8220*I tell you,\uc1\u8221* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8220*if you have faith, without ever a doubt, you will do what not only what has been done to the fig tree, but, even if you should say to this hill \uc1\u8216*Be lifted up and hurled into the sea!\uc1\u8217* it would be done.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And whatever you ask for in your prayers will, if you have faith, be granted you.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}After Jesus had come into the Temple Courts, the chief priests and the elders of the people came up to him as he was teaching, and said, \uc1\u8220*What authority have you to do these things? Who gave you this authority?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}\uc1\u8220*I, too,\uc1\u8221* said Jesus in reply, \uc1\u8220*will ask you one question; if you will give me an answer to it, then I, also, will tell you what authority I have to act as I do.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}It is about John\uc1\u8217*s baptism. What was its origin? Divine or human?\uc1\u8221* But they began arguing among themselves, \uc1\u8220*If we say \uc1\u8216*divine,\uc1\u8217* he will say to us \uc1\u8216*Why then didn\uc1\u8217*t you believe him?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}But if we say \uc1\u8216*human,\uc1\u8217* we are afraid of the people, for everyone regards John as a prophet.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}So the answer they gave Jesus was \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*We do not know.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 \uc1\u8220*Then I,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*refuse to tell you what authority I have to do these things.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}What do you think of this? There was a man who had two sons. He went to the elder and said \uc1\u8216*Go and work in the vineyard today my son.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}\uc1\u8216*Yes, sir,\uc1\u8217* he answered; but he did not go.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Then the father went to the second son, and said the same. \uc1\u8216*I will not,\uc1\u8217* he answered; but afterward he was sorry and went.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Which of the two sons did as his father wished?\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8220*The second,\uc1\u8221* they said. \uc1\u8220*I tell you,\uc1\u8221* added Jesus, \uc1\u8220*that tax collectors and prostitutes are going into the kingdom of God before you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}For when John came to you, walking in the path of righteousness, you did not believe him, but tax collectors and prostitutes did; and yet you, though you saw this, even then were not sorry, nor did you believe him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}\uc1\u8220*Listen to another parable. A man, who was an employer, once planted a vineyard, put a fence around it, dug a winepress in it, built a tower, and then let it out to tenants and went abroad.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}When the time for the grape harvest drew near, he sent his servants to the tenants, to receive his share of the produce.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}But the tenants seized his servants, beat one, killed another, and stoned a third.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}A second time the owner sent some servants, a larger number than before, and the tenants treated them in the same way.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}As a last resource he sent his son to them. \uc1\u8216*They will respect my son,\uc1\u8217* he said.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}But the tenants, on seeing his son, said to each other \uc1\u8216*Here is the heir! Come, let us kill him, and get his inheritance.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}So they seized him, and threw him outside the vineyard, and killed him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}Now, when the owner of the vineyard comes, what will he do to those tenants?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}\uc1\u8220*Miserable wretches!\uc1\u8221* they exclaimed, \uc1\u8220*he will put them to a miserable death, and he will let out the vineyard to other tenants, who will pay him his share of the produce at the proper times.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}Then Jesus added, \uc1\u8220*Have you never read in the scriptures? \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*The stone which the builders despised \uc1\u8211* has now itself become the cornerstone. This cornerstone has come from the Lord, and is marvelous in our eyes.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}That, I tell you, is why the kingdom of God will be taken from you, and given to a nation that does produce the fruit of the kingdom.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}Yes, and he who falls on this stone will be dashed to pieces, while anyone on whom it falls \uc1\u8211* it will scatter him as dust.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}After listening to these parables, the chief priests and the Pharisees saw that it was about them that he was speaking;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}yet, although eager to arrest him, they were afraid of the crowds, who regarded him as a prophet.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 22}Once more Jesus spoke to them in parables.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8220*The kingdom of heaven,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*may be compared to a king who gave a banquet in honor of his son\uc1\u8217*s wedding.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}He sent his servants to call those who had been invited to the banquet, but they were unwilling to come.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}A second time he sent some servants, with orders to say to those who had been invited \uc1\u8216*I have prepared my meal, my cattle and fat beasts are killed and everything is ready; come to the banquet.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}They, however, took no notice, but went off, one to their farm, another to their business;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}while the rest, seizing his servants, ill-treated them and killed them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The king, in anger, sent his troops, put those murderers to death, and set their city on fire.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Then he said to his servants \uc1\u8216*The banquet is prepared, but those who were invited were not worthy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}So go to the cross-roads, and invite everyone you find to the banquet.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}The servants went out into the roads and collected all the people whom they found, whether bad or good; and the bridal-hall was filled with guests.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But, when the king went in to see his guests, he noticed there a man who had not put on a wedding-robe.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}So he said to him \uc1\u8216*My friend, how is it that you came in here without a wedding-robe?\uc1\u8217* The man was speechless.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then the king said to the attendants \uc1\u8216*Tie him hand and foot, and put him out into the darkness outside, where there will be weeping and grinding of teeth.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}For many are called, but few chosen.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Then the Pharisees went away and conferred together as to how they might lay a trap for Jesus in the course of conversation.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}They sent their disciples, with the Herodians, to say to him, \uc1\u8220*Teacher, we know that you are an honest person, and that you teach the way of God honestly, and are not afraid of anyone; for you pay no regard to a person\uc1\u8217*s position.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Tell us, then, what you think. Are we right in paying taxes to the Emperor, or not?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Perceiving their malice, Jesus answered, \uc1\u8220*Why are you testing me, you hypocrites?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Show me the coin with which the tax is paid.\uc1\u8221* And, when they had brought him a coin,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}he asked, \uc1\u8220*Whose head and title are these?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8220*The Emperor\uc1\u8217*s,\uc1\u8221* they answered, at which he said to them, \uc1\u8220*Then pay to the Emperor what belongs to the Emperor, and to God what belongs to God.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}They wondered at his answer, and left him alone and went away.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}That same day some Sadducees came up to Jesus, maintaining that there is no resurrection. Their question was this, \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}\uc1\u8220*Teacher, Moses said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*should a man die without children, the man\uc1\u8217*s brother will become the husband of the widow, and raise a family for his brother.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Now we had living among us seven brothers; of whom the eldest married and died, and, as he had no family, left his wife for his brother.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}The same thing happened to the second and the third brothers, and indeed to all the seven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}The woman herself died last of all.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}At the resurrection, then, whose wife will she be out of the seven, all of them having been married to her?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}\uc1\u8220*Your mistake,\uc1\u8221* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8220*is due to your ignorance of the scriptures, and of the power of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}For at the resurrection there is no marrying or being married, but all who rise are as angels in heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}As to the resurrection of the dead, have you not read these words of God \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}\uc1\u8216*I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob\uc1\u8217*? He is not the God of dead people, but of living.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}The crowds, who had been listening to him, were greatly struck with his teaching.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}When the Pharisees heard that Jesus had silenced the Sadducees, they collected together.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Then one of them, a Student of the Law, to test him, asked this question \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}\uc1\u8220*Teacher, what is the greatest commandment in the Law?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}His answer was, \uc1\u8220*You must love the Lord your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your mind.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}This is the great first commandment.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}The second, which is like it, is this \uc1\u8211* You must love your neighbor as you love yourself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}On these two commandments hang all the Law and the prophets.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}Before the Pharisees separated, Jesus put this question to them \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}\uc1\u8220*What do you think about the Christ? Whose son is he?\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8220*David\uc1\u8217*s,\uc1\u8221* they said.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}\uc1\u8220*How is it, then,\uc1\u8221* Jesus replied, \uc1\u8220*that David, speaking under inspiration, calls him \uc1\u8216*lord,\uc1\u8217* in the passage \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}\uc1\u8216*The Lord said to my Lord: Sit at my right hand, until I put your enemies beneath your feet\uc1\u8217*?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}Since, then, David calls him \uc1\u8216*lord,\uc1\u8217* how is he David\uc1\u8217*s son?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}No one could say a word in answer; nor did anyone after that day venture to question him further.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 23}Then Jesus, speaking to the crowds and to his disciples, said,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8220*The teachers of the Law and the Pharisees now occupy the chair of Moses.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Therefore practice and lay to heart everything that they preach but do not practice.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}While they make up heavy loads and pile them on other people\uc1\u8217*s shoulder\uc1\u8217*s they decline, themselves, to lift a finger to move them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}All their actions are done to attract attention. They widen their phylacteries, and increase the size of their tassels,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}and like to have the place of honor at dinner, and the best seats in the synagogues,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}and to be greeted in the markets with respect, and to be called \uc1\u8216*Rabbi\uc1\u8217* by everybody.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}But do not allow yourselves to be called \uc1\u8216*Rabbi,\uc1\u8217* for you have only one teacher, and you yourselves are all brothers and sisters.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}And do not call anyone on the earth your \uc1\u8216*Father,\uc1\u8217* for your have only one Father, the heavenly Father.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Nor must you allow yourselves to be called \uc1\u8216*leaders,\uc1\u8217* for you have only one leader, the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The person who wants to be the greatest among you must be your servant.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Whoever exalts themselves will be humbled, and whoever humbles themselves will be exalted.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}But alas for you, teachers of the Law and Pharisees, hypocrites that you are! You turn the key of the kingdom of heaven in people\uc1\u8217*s faces. For you do not go in yourselves, and do not allow those who try to go in to do so.{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}   Some later manuscripts add: Alas for you teachers of the law and Pharisees, hypocrites! You devour widows\uc1\u8217* property, and pray long prayers just for show! This is why you will receive a more severe punishment. }{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Alas for you, teachers of the law and Pharisees, hypocrites that you are! You scour land and sea to make a single convert, and, when they are gained, you make them twice as deserving of Gehenna as you are yourselves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Alas for you, you blind guides! You say \uc1\u8216*if any swear by the Temple, their oath counts for nothing; but, if anyone swears by the gold of the Temple, their oath is binding them\uc1\u8217*!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Fools that you are and blind! Which is the more important? The gold? Or the Temple which has given sacredness to the gold?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}You say, too, \uc1\u8216*If anyone swears by the altar, their oath counts for nothing, but, if anyone swears by the offering placed on it, their oath is binding on them\uc1\u8217*!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Blind indeed! Which is the more important? The offering? Or the altar which gives sacredness to the offering?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Therefore a person, swearing by the altar, swears by it and by all that is on it,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}and a person, swearing by the Temple, swears by it and by him who dwells in it,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}while a person, swearing by heaven, swears by the throne of God, and by him who sits on it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Alas for you, teachers of the Law and Pharisees, hypocrites that you are! You pay tithes on mint, fennel, and caraway seed, and have neglected the weightier matters of the Law \uc1\u8211* justice, mercy, and good faith. These last you ought to have put into practice, without neglecting the first.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}You blind guides, to strain out a gnat and to swallow a camel!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Alas for you, teachers of the Law and Pharisees, hypocrites that you are! You clean the outside of the cup and the dish, but inside they are filled with the results of greed and self-indulgence.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}You blind Pharisee! First clean the inside of the cup and the dish, so that the outside may become clean as well.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Alas for you, teachers of the Law and Pharisees, hypocrites that you are! You are like whitewashed tombs, which indeed look fair outside, while inside they are filled with dead people\uc1\u8217*s bones and all kinds of filth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}It is the same with you. Outwardly, and to others, you have the look of religious people, but inwardly you are full of hypocrisy and sin.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Alas for you, teachers of the Law and Pharisees, hypocrites that you are! You build the tombs of the prophets, and decorate the monuments of religious people,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}and say \uc1\u8216*Had we been living in the days of our ancestors, we should have taken no part in their murder of the prophets!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}By doing this you are furnishing evidence against yourselves that you are true children of the people who murdered the prophets.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Go on then, finish what your ancestors began!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}You snakes and children of snakes! How can you escape being sentenced to Gehenna?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}That is why I send you prophets, wise people, and teachers of the Law, some of whom you will crucify and kill, and some of whom you will scourge in your synagogues, and persecute from town to town;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}so that on your heads may fall every drop of innocent blood split on earth, from the blood of innocent Abel down to that of Zechariah, Barachiah\uc1\u8217*s son, whom you murdered between the Temple and the altar.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}All this, I tell you, will come home to the present generation.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Jerusalem! Jerusalem! She who slays the prophets and stones the messengers sent to her \uc1\u8211* Oh, how often have I wished to gather your children around me, as a hen gathers her brood under her wings, and you would not come!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}Verily, your house is left to you desolate!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}For nevermore, I tell you, will you see me, until you say \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Blessed is He who comes in the name of the Lord!\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 24}Leaving the Temple Courts, Jesus was walking away, when his disciples came up to draw his attention to the Temple buildings.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8220*Do you see all these things?\uc1\u8221* was his answer. \uc1\u8220*I tell you, not a single stone will be left here on another, which will not be thrown down,\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}so, while Jesus was sitting on the Mount of Olives, his disciples came up to him privately and said, \uc1\u8220*Tell us when this will be, and what will be the sign of your coming, and of the close of the age.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Jesus replied to them, \uc1\u8220*See that no one leads you astray;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}for, many will take my name, and come saying \uc1\u8216*I am the Christ,\uc1\u8217* and will lead many astray.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}You will hear of wars and rumors of wars; take care not to be alarmed, for such things must occur; but the end is not yet here.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}For nation will rise against nation and kingdom against kingdom, and there will be famines and earthquakes in various places.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}All this, however, will be but the beginning of the birth pangs!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}When that time comes, they will give you up to persecution, and will put you to death, and you will be hated by all nations because of me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And then many will fall away, and will betray one another, and hate one another.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Many false prophets, also, will appear and lead many astray;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}and, owing to the increase of wickedness, the love of most will grow cold.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Yet the person who endures to the end will be saved.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}This good news of the kingdom will be proclaimed throughout the world as a witness to all nations; and then will come the end.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}As soon, then, as you see \uc1\u8216*the Foul Desecration,\uc1\u8217* mentioned by the prophet Daniel, standing in the Holy place,\uc1\u8221* (the reader must consider what this means){\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8220*then those of you who are in Judea must take refuge in the mountains;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}and a man on the housetop must not go down to get the things that are in his house;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}nor must one who is on their farm turn back to get his cloak.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Alas for pregnant women, and for those who are nursing infants in those days!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Pray, too, that your flight may not take place in winter, nor on a Sabbath;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}for that will be a time of great distress, the like of which has not occurred from the beginning of the world down to the present time \uc1\u8211* no, nor ever will again.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Had not those days been limited, not a single soul would escape; but for the sake of God\uc1\u8217*s people a limit will be put to them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}At that time, if anyone should say to you \uc1\u8216*Look! Here is the Christ!\uc1\u8217* or \uc1\u8216*Here he is!\uc1\u8217*, do not believe it;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}for false Christs and false prophets will arise, and will display great signs and marvels, so that, were it possible, even God\uc1\u8217*s people would be led astray.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Remember, I have told you beforehand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Therefore, if people say to you \uc1\u8216*He is in the wilderness!\uc1\u8217*, do not go out there; or \uc1\u8216*He is in an inner room!\uc1\u8217*, do not believe it;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}for, just as lightning will start from the east and flash across to the west, so will it be with the coming of the Son of Man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Wherever a dead body lies, there will the vultures flock.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Immediately after the distress of those days, the sun will be darkened, the moon will not give her light, the stars will fall from the heavens, and the forces of the heavens will be convulsed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Then will appear the sign of the Son of Man in the heavens; and all the peoples of the earth will mourn, when they see the Son of Man coming on the clouds of the heavens, with power and great glory;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}and he will send his angels, with a great trumpet, and they will gather his people around him from the four winds, from one end of heaven to the other.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}\uc1\u8220*Learn the lesson taught by the fig tree. As soon as its branches are full of sap, and it is bursting into leaf, you know that summer is near.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}And so may you, as soon as you see all these things, know that he is at your doors.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}I tell you, even the present generation will not pass away, until all these things have taken place.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}The heavens and the earth will pass away, but my words will never pass away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}But about that day and hour, no one knows \uc1\u8211* not even the angels of heaven, not even the Son \uc1\u8211* but only the Father himself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}For, just as in the days of Noah, so will it be at the coming of the Son of Man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}In those days before the flood they went on eating and drinking, marrying and being married, up to the very day on which Noah entered the ark,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}taking not notice until the flood came and swept them one and all away; and so will it be at the coming of the Son of Man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}At that time, of two men on a farm one will be taken and one left;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}of two women grinding with a hand-mill one will be taken and one left.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}Therefore watch; for you cannot be sure on what day your Master is coming.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}But this you do know, that, had the owner of the house known at what time of night the thief was coming, they would have been on the watch, and would not have allowed their house to be broken into.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}Therefore, you must also prepare, since it is just when you are least expecting him that the Son of Man will come.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}Who, then is that trustworthy, careful servant, who has been placed by their master over his household, to give them their food at the proper time?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}Happy will that servant be whom their master, when he comes home, will find doing this.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}I tell you that their master will put them in charge of the whole of his property.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}But, should the servant be a bad servant, and say to themselves \uc1\u8216*My master is a long time in coming,\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}and begin to beat their fellow servants, and eat and drink with drunkards,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}that servant\uc1\u8217*s master will come on a day when they do not expect him, and at an hour of which they are unaware,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}and will flog the servant severely, and assign them their place among the hypocrites, where there will be weeping and grinding of teeth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 25}\uc1\u8220*Then the kingdom of heaven will be like ten bridesmaids who took their lamps and went out to meet the groom.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Five of them were foolish, and five were prudent.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}The foolish ones took their lamps, but took no oil with them;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}while the prudent ones, besides taking their lamps, took oil in their jars.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}As the groom was late in coming, they all became drowsy, and slept.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But at midnight a shout was raised \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*The groom is coming! Come out to meet him!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Then all the bridesmaids woke up and trimmed their lamps,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}and the foolish said to the prudent \uc1\u8216*Give us some of your oil; our lamps are going out.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}But the prudent ones answered \uc1\u8216*No, There may not be enough for you and for us. Go instead to those who sell it, and buy for yourselves.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}But while they were on their way to buy it, the groom came; and the bridesmaids who were ready went in with him to the banquet, and the door was shut.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Afterward the other bridesmaids came. \uc1\u8216*Sir, Sir,\uc1\u8217* they said, \uc1\u8216*open the door to us!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}But the groom answered \uc1\u8216*I tell you, I do not know you.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Therefore watch, since you know neither the day nor the hour.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}\uc1\u8220*For it is as though a man, going on his travels, called his servants, and gave his property into their charge.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}He gave five bags of gold to one, two to another, and one bag to a third, in proportion to the ability of each. Then he set out on his travels.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}The servant who had received the five bags of gold went at once and traded with it, and made another five bags.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}So, too, the servant who had received the two bags of gold made another two bags.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}But the servant who had received the one bag went and dug a hole in the ground, and hid his master\uc1\u8217*s money.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}After a long time the master of those servants returned, and settled accounts with them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}The servant who had received the five bags of gold came up and brought five bags more. \uc1\u8216*Sir,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*you entrusted me with five bags of gold; look, I have made another five bags!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8216*Well done, good, trustworthy servant!\uc1\u8217* said his master. \uc1\u8216*You have been trustworthy with a small sum; now I will place a large one in your hands; come and share your master\uc1\u8217*s joy!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Then the one who had received the two bags of gold came up and said \uc1\u8216*Sir, you entrusted me with two bags pounds; look, I have made another two!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8216*Well done, good, trustworthy servant!\uc1\u8217* said his master. \uc1\u8216*You have been trustworthy with a small sum; now I will place a large one in your hands; come and share your master\uc1\u8217*s joy!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}The man who had received the single bag of gold came up, too, and said \uc1\u8216*Sir, I knew that you were a hard man; you reap where you have not sown, and gather up where you have not winnowed;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}and, in my fear, I went and hid your money in the ground; look, here is what belongs to you!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}\uc1\u8216*You lazy, worthless servant!\uc1\u8217* was his master\uc1\u8217*s reply. \uc1\u8216*You knew that I reap where I have not sown, and gather up where I have not winnowed?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Then you ought to have placed my money in the hands of bankers, and I, on my return, should have received my money, with interest.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Therefore,\uc1\u8217* he continued, \uc1\u8216*take away from him the one bag of gold, and give it to the one who has the ten bags.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}For, to him who has, more will be given, and he will have abundance; but, as for him who has nothing, even what he has will be taken away from him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}As for the useless servant, put him out into the darkness outside, where there will be weeping and grinding of teeth.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}\uc1\u8220*When the Son of Man has come in his glory and all the angels with him, then he will take his seat on his throne of glory;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}and all the nations will be gathered before him, and he will separate the people \uc1\u8211* just as a shepherd separates sheep from goats \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}placing the sheep on his right hand, and the goats on his left.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Then the king will say to those on his right \uc1\u8216*Come, you who are blessed by my Father, enter into possession of the kingdom prepared for you ever since the beginning of the world.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}For, when I was hungry, you gave me food; when I was thirsty, you gave me drink; when I was a stranger, you took me to your homes;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}when I was naked, you clothed me; when I fell ill, you visited me; and when I was in prison, you came to me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Then the righteous will answer \uc1\u8216*Lord, when did we see you hungry, and feed you? Or thirsty, and give you a drink?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}When did we see you a stranger, and take you to our homes? Or naked, and clothe you?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}When did we see you ill, or in prison, and come to you?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}And the king will reply \uc1\u8216*I tell you, as often as you did it to one of these my brothers or sisters, however unimportant they seemed, you did it to me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}Then he will say to those on his left \uc1\u8216*Go from my presence, accursed, into the permanent fire which has been prepared for the devil and his angels.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}For, when I was hungry, you gave me no food; when I was thirsty, you gave me no drink;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}when I was a stranger, you did not take me to your homes; when I was naked, you did not clothe me; and, when I was ill and in prison, you did not visit me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}Then they, in their turn, will answer \uc1\u8216*Lord, when did we see you hungry, or thirsty, or a stranger, or naked, or ill, or in prison, and did not supply your wants?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}And then he will reply \uc1\u8216*I tell you, as often as you failed to do it to one of these, however unimportant, you failed to do it to me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}And these last will go away into lasting correction, but the righteous into lasting life.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 26}When Jesus had finished teaching all of that, he said to his disciples,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8220*You know that in two days time the Festival of the Passover will be here; and that the Son of Man is to be given up to be crucified.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Then the chief priests and the elders of the people met in the house of the high priest, who was called Caiaphas,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and plotted together to arrest Jesus by stealth and put him to death;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}but they said, \uc1\u8220*Not during the Festival, or the people may riot.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}After Jesus had reached Bethany, and while he was in the house of Simon the leper,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}a woman came up to him with an alabaster jar of very costly perfume, and poured the perfume on his head as he sat at the table.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The disciples were indignant at seeing this. \uc1\u8220*What is this waste for?\uc1\u8221* they exclaimed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}\uc1\u8220*It could have been sold for a large sum, and the money given to poor people.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8220*Why are you troubling the woman?\uc1\u8221* Jesus said, when he noticed it. \uc1\u8220*For this is a beautiful deed that she has done to me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}You always have the poor with you, but you will not always have me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}In pouring this perfume on my body, she prepares me for my burial.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}I tell you, wherever, in the whole world, this good news is proclaimed, what this woman has done will be told in memory of her.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}It was then that one of the Twelve, named Judas Iscariot, made his way to the chief priests,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}and said \uc1\u8220*What are you willing to give me, if I betray Jesus to you?\uc1\u8221* The Priests counted him out thirty pieces of silver as payment.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}So from that time Judas looked for an opportunity to betray Jesus.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}On the first day of the Festival of the unleavened bread, the disciples came up to Jesus, and said, \uc1\u8220*Where do you wish us to make preparations for you to eat the Passover?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8220*Go into the city to a certain man,\uc1\u8221* he answered, \uc1\u8220*and say to him \uc1\u8216*The teacher says \uc1\u8211* My time is near. I will keep the Passover with my disciples at your house.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}The disciples did as Jesus directed them, and prepared the Passover.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}In the evening Jesus took his place with the twelve disciples,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}and, while they were eating, he said, \uc1\u8220*I tell you that one of you will betray me.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}In great grief they began to say to him, one by one, \uc1\u8220*Can it be I, Master?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8220*The one who dipped his bread beside me in the dish,\uc1\u8221* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8220*is the one who will betray me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}True, the Son of Man must go, as scripture says of him, yet alas for that man by whom the Son of Man is being betrayed! For that man it would be better never to have been born!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Judas, who was betraying him, turned to him and said, \uc1\u8220*Can it be I, Rabbi?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 \uc1\u8220*It is,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}While they were eating, Jesus took some bread, and, after saying the blessing, broke it and, as he gave it to his disciples, said, \uc1\u8220*Take it and eat it; this is my body.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Then he took a cup, and, after saying the thanksgiving, gave it to them, with the words, \uc1\u8220*Drink from it, all of you;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}for this is my covenant blood, which is poured out for many for the forgiveness of sins.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}I tell you that I will never, after this, drink of this juice of the grape, until that day when I will drink it new with you in the kingdom of my Father.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}They then sang a hymn, and went out to the Mount of Olives.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Then Jesus said to them, \uc1\u8220*Even you will all fall away from me tonight. Scripture says \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*I will strike down the shepherd, and the sheep of the flock will be scattered.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}But, after I have risen, I will go before you into Galilee.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}\uc1\u8220*If everyone else falls away from you,\uc1\u8221* Peter answered, \uc1\u8220*I will never fall away!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}\uc1\u8220*I tell you,\uc1\u8221* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8220*that this very night, before the cock crows, you will disown me three times!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}\uc1\u8220*Even if I must die with you,\uc1\u8221* Peter exclaimed, \uc1\u8220*I will never disown you!\uc1\u8221* All the disciples spoke in the same way.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Then Jesus came with them to a garden called Gethsemane, and he said to his disciples, \uc1\u8220*Sit down here while I go and pray over there.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Taking with him Peter and the two sons of Zebedee, he began to show signs of sadness and deep distress of mind.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}\uc1\u8220*I am sad at heart,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*sad even to death; wait here and watch with me.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}Going on a little further, he threw himself on his face in prayer. \uc1\u8220*My Father,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*if it is possible, let me be spared this cup; only, not as I will, but as you will.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}Then he came to his disciples, and found them asleep. \uc1\u8220*What!\uc1\u8221* he said to Peter, \uc1\u8220*could none of you watch with me for one hour?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}Watch and pray so that you don\uc1\u8217*t fall into temptation. True, the spirit is eager, but human nature is weak.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}Again, a second time, he went away, and prayed. \uc1\u8220*My Father,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*if I cannot be spared this cup, but must drink it, your will be done!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}And coming back again he found them asleep, for their eyes were heavy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}So he left them, and went away again, and prayed a third time, again saying the same words.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}Then he came to the disciples, and said, \uc1\u8220*Sleep on now, and rest yourselves. Look \uc1\u8211* my time is close at hand, and the Son of Man is being betrayed into the hands of wicked people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}Up, and let us be going. Look! My betrayer is close at hand.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}And, while he was still speaking, Judas, who was one of the Twelve, came in sight; and with him was a great crowd of people, with swords and clubs, sent from the chief priests and elders of the people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}Now the betrayer had arranged a signal with them. \uc1\u8220*The man whom I kiss,\uc1\u8221* he had said, \uc1\u8220*will be the one; arrest him.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}So he went up to Jesus at once, and exclaimed, \uc1\u8220*Welcome, Rabbi!\uc1\u8221* and kissed him;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}at which Jesus said to him, \uc1\u8220*Friend, do what you have come for.\uc1\u8221* The men went up, seized Jesus, and arrested him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}Suddenly one of those who were with Jesus stretched out his hand, and drew his sword, and striking the high priest\uc1\u8217*s servant, cut off his ear.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}\uc1\u8220*Sheathe your sword,\uc1\u8221* Jesus said, \uc1\u8220*for all who draw the sword will be put to the sword.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}Do you think that I cannot ask my Father for help, when he would at once send to my aid more than twelve legions of angels?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}But in that case how would the scriptures be fulfilled, which say that this must be?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}Jesus at the same time said to the crowds, \uc1\u8220*Have you come out, as if after a robber, with swords and clubs, to take me? I have sat teaching day after day in the Temple Courts, and yet you did not arrest me.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}The whole of this occurred in fulfillment of the prophetic scriptures. Then the disciples all forsook him and fled.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 57}Those who had arrested Jesus took him to Caiaphas, the high priest, where the teachers of the Law and elders had assembled.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 58}Peter followed him at a distance as far as the high priest\uc1\u8217*s courtyard, to see the outcome.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 59}Meanwhile the chief priests and the whole of the High Council were trying to get such false evidence against Jesus, as would warrant putting him to death,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 60}but they did not find any, although many came forward with false evidence. Later on, however, two men came forward and said,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 61}\uc1\u8220*This man said \uc1\u8216*I am able to destroy the Temple of God, and to build it in three days.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 62}Then the high priest stood up, and said to Jesus, \uc1\u8220*Have you no answer? What is this evidence which these men are giving against you?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 63}But Jesus remained silent. The high priest said to him, \uc1\u8220*I order you, by the living God, to tell us whether you are the Christ, the Son of God.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 64}\uc1\u8220*It is true,\uc1\u8221* Jesus answered, \uc1\u8220*Moreover I tell you all that hereafter you will see the Son of Man sitting on the right hand of the Almighty, and coming on the clouds of the heavens.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 65}Then the high priest tore his robes. \uc1\u8220*This is blasphemy!\uc1\u8221* he exclaimed. \uc1\u8220*Why do we want any more witnesses? You have just heard his blasphemy!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 66}What is your decision?\uc1\u8221* They answered, \uc1\u8220*He deserves death.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 67}Then they spat in his face, and struck him, while others dealt blows at him, saying as they did so,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 68}\uc1\u8220*Now play the prophet for us, you Christ! Who was it that struck you?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 69}Peter, meanwhile, was sitting outside in the courtyard; and a maidservant came up to him, and exclaimed, \uc1\u8220*Why, you were with Jesus the Galilean!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 70}But Peter denied it before them all. \uc1\u8220*I do not know what you mean,\uc1\u8221* he replied.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 71}When he had gone out into the gateway, another maid saw him, and said to those who were there, \uc1\u8220*This man was with Jesus of Nazareth!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 72}Again he denied it with an oath, \uc1\u8220*I do not know the man!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 73}But soon afterward those who were standing by came up and said to Peter, \uc1\u8220*You also are certainly one of them; why, even your way of speaking proves it!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 74}Then Peter said, \uc1\u8220*I swear that I do not know the man! May God punish me if I am lying!\uc1\u8221* At that moment a cock crowed;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 75}and Peter remembered the words which Jesus had said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Before a cock has crowed, you will disown me three times\uc1\u8217*; and he went outside, and wept bitterly.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 27}At daybreak all the chief priests and the elders of the people consulted together against Jesus, to bring about his death.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}They put him in chains and led him away, and gave him up to the Roman Governor, Pilate.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Then Judas, who betrayed him, seeing that Jesus was condemned, repented of what he had done, and returned the thirty pieces of silver to the chief priests and elders.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}\uc1\u8220*I did wrong in betraying a good man to his death,\uc1\u8221* he said. \uc1\u8220*What has that to do with us?\uc1\u8221* they replied. \uc1\u8220*You must see to that yourself.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Judas flung down the pieces of silver in the Temple, and left; and went away and hanged himself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}The chief priests took the pieces of silver, but they said, \uc1\u8220*We must not put them into the Temple treasury, because they are blood-money.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}So, after consultation, they used it to buy the \uc1\u8216*Potter\uc1\u8217*s Field\uc1\u8217* as a burial ground for foreigners,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}and that is why that field is called the \uc1\u8216*Field of Blood\uc1\u8217* to this very day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Then it was that these words spoken by the prophet Jeremiah were fulfilled \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*They took the thirty pieces of silver, the price set on him by the people of Israel,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}and gave them for the potter\uc1\u8217*s field, as the Lord commanded me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Meanwhile Jesus was brought before the Roman Governor. \uc1\u8220*Are you the king of the Jews?\uc1\u8221* asked the Governor. \uc1\u8220*It is true,\uc1\u8221* answered Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}While charges were being brought against him by the chief priests and elders, Jesus made no reply.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then Pilate said to him, \uc1\u8220*Don\uc1\u8217*t you hear how many accusations they are making against you?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Yet Jesus made no reply \uc1\u8211* not even a single word; at which the Governor was greatly astonished.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Now, at the feast, the Governor was accustomed to grant the people the release of any one prisoner whom they might choose.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}At that time they had a notorious prisoner called Barabbas.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}So, when the people had collected, Pilate said to them, \uc1\u8220*Which do you wish me to release for you? Barabbas? Or Jesus who is called \uc1\u8216*Christ\uc1\u8217*?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}For he knew that it was out of jealousy that they had given Jesus up to him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}While he was still on the Bench, his wife sent this message to him \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Do not have anything to do with that good man, for I have been very much troubled today in a dream because of him.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}But the chief priests and elders persuaded the crowds to ask for Barabbas, and to kill Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}The Governor, however, said to them, \uc1\u8220*Which of these two do you wish me to release for you?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 \uc1\u8220*Barabbas,\uc1\u8221* they answered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}\uc1\u8220*What then,\uc1\u8221* Pilate asked, \uc1\u8220*should I do with Jesus who is called \uc1\u8216*Christ?\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8220*Crucify him,\uc1\u8221* they all replied.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8220*Why, what harm has he done?\uc1\u8221* he asked. But they kept shouting furiously, \uc1\u8220*Crucify him!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}When Pilate saw that his efforts were unavailing, but that, on the contrary, a riot was beginning, he took some water, and washed his hands in the sight of the crowd, saying as he did so, \uc1\u8220*I am not answerable for this bloodshed; you must see to it yourselves.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}And all the people answered, \uc1\u8220*His blood be on our heads and on our children\uc1\u8217*s!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Then Pilate released Barabbas to them, but Jesus he had scourged, and gave him up to be crucified.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}After that, the Governor\uc1\u8217*s soldiers took Jesus with them into the Government house, and gathered the whole garrison around him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}They stripped him, and put on him a red military cloak,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}and having twisted some thorns into a crown, put it on his head, and a rod in his right hand, and then, going down on their knees before him, they mocked him. \uc1\u8220*Long life to you, king of the Jews!\uc1\u8221* they said.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}They spat at him and, taking the rod, kept striking him on the head;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}and, when they had left off mocking him, they took off the military cloak, and put his own clothes on him, and led him away to be crucified.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}As they were on their way out, they came upon a man from Cyrene called Simon, and they compelled him to go with them to carry the cross.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}On reaching a place named Golgotha (a place named from its likeness to a skull),{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}they gave him some wine to drink which had been mixed with gall; but after tasting it, Jesus refused to drink it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}When they had crucified him, they divided his clothes among them by casting lots.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Then they sat down, and kept watch over him there.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Above his head they fixed the accusation against him written out \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*THIS IS JESUS THE KING OF THE JEWS.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}At the same time two robbers were crucified with him, one on the right, the other on the left.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}The passers-by railed at him, shaking their heads as they said,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}\uc1\u8220*You who would \uc1\u8216*destroy the Temple and build one in three days,\uc1\u8217* save yourself! If you are God\uc1\u8217*s Son, come down from the cross!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}In the same way the chief priests, with the Teachers of the Law and elders, said in mockery,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}\uc1\u8220*He saved others, but he cannot save himself! He is the \uc1\u8216*king of Israel\uc1\u8217*! Why doesn\uc1\u8217*t he come down from the cross now, then we will believe in him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}He has trusted in God; if God wants him, let him deliver him now; for he said \uc1\u8216*I am God\uc1\u8217*s Son.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}Even the robbers, who were crucified with him, insulted him in the same way.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}After midday a darkness came over all the country, lasting until three in the afternoon.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}About three Jesus called out loudly, \uc1\u8220*Eloi, Eloi, lema sabacthani\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211* that is to say, \uc1\u8216*My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}Some of those standing by heard this, and said, \uc1\u8220*The man is calling for Elijah!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}One of them immediately ran and took a sponge, and, filling it with common wine, put it on the end of a rod, and offered it to him to drink.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}But the rest said, \uc1\u8220*Wait and let us see if Elijah is coming to save him.\uc1\u8221*{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn    Some later manuscripts add: However another man took a spear, and pierced his side; and water and blood flowed from it. }{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}But Jesus, uttering another loud cry, gave up his spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}Suddenly the Temple curtain was torn in two from top to bottom, the earth shook, the rocks were torn asunder,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}the tombs opened, and the bodies of many of God\uc1\u8217*s people who had fallen asleep rose,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}and they, leaving their tombs, went, after the resurrection of Jesus, into the Holy City, and appeared to many people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}The Roman centurion, and the men with him who were watching Jesus, on seeing the earthquake and all that was happening, became greatly frightened and exclaimed, \uc1\u8220*This must indeed have been God\uc1\u8217*s Son!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}There were many women there, watching from a distance, who had accompanied Jesus from Galilee and had been attending on him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}Among them were Mary of Magdala, Mary the mother of James and Joseph, and the mother of Zebedee\uc1\u8217*s sons.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 57}When evening had fallen, there came a rich man from  Arimathea, named Joseph, who had himself become a disciple of Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 58}He went to see Pilate, and asked for the body of Jesus. Pilate ordered it to be given him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 59}So Joseph took the body, and wrapped it in a clean linen sheet,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 60}and laid it in his newly made tomb which he had cut in the rock; and, before he left, he rolled a great stone against the entrance of the tomb.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 61}Mary of Magdala and the other Mary remained behind, sitting in front of the grave.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 62}The next day \uc1\u8211* that is, the day following the Preparation-day \uc1\u8211* the chief priests and Pharisees came in a body to Pilate, and said,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 63}\uc1\u8220*Sir, we remember that, during his lifetime, that impostor said \uc1\u8216*I will rise after three days.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 64}So order the tomb to be made secure until the third day. Otherwise his disciples may come and steal him, and then say to the people \uc1\u8216*He has risen from the dead,\uc1\u8217* when the latest imposture will be worse than the first.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 65}\uc1\u8220*You may have a guard,\uc1\u8221* was Pilate\uc1\u8217*s reply. \uc1\u8220*Go and make the tomb as secure as you can.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 66}So they went and made the tomb secure, by sealing the stone, in presence of the guard.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Risen Life

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 28}After the Sabbath, as the first day of the week began to dawn, Mary of Magdala and the other Mary had gone to look at the grave,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}when suddenly a great earthquake occurred. For an angel of the Lord descended from heaven, and came and rolled away the stone, and seated himself on it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}His appearance was as dazzling as lightning, and his clothing was as white as snow;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and, in their terror of him, the men on guard trembled violently and became like dead men.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}But the angel, addressing the women, said, \uc1\u8220*You need not be afraid. I know that it is Jesus, who was crucified, for whom you are looking.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}He is not here; for he has risen, as he said he would. Come, and see the place where he was lying;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}and then go quickly and say to his disciples \uc1\u8216*He has risen from the dead, and is going before you into Galilee; there you will see him.\uc1\u8217* Remember, I have told you.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}They left the tomb quickly, in awe and great joy, and ran to tell the news to the disciples.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Suddenly Jesus met them. \uc1\u8220*Welcome!\uc1\u8221* he said. The women went up to him, and clasped his feet, bowing to the ground before him. Then Jesus said to them,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8220*Do not be afraid; go and tell my brothers and sisters to set out for Galilee, and they will see me there.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}While they were still on their way, some of the guard came into the city, and reported to the chief priests everything that had happened.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}So they and the elders met and, after holding a consultation, gave a large sum of money to the soldiers,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}and told them to say that his disciples came in the night, and stole him while they were asleep;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}\uc1\u8220*And should this matter come before the Governor,\uc1\u8221* they added, \uc1\u8220*we will satisfy him, and see that you have nothing to fear.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}So the soldiers took the money, and did as they were instructed. This story spread widely; the people of Judea still tell it today.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}The eleven disciples went to Galilee, to the mountain where Jesus told them to meet him;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}and, when they saw him, they bowed to the ground before him; although some felt doubtful.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Then Jesus came up, and spoke to them, saying, \uc1\u8220*All authority in heaven and on the earth has been given to me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Therefore go and make disciples of all the nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}and teaching them to lay to heart all the commands that I have given you; and, remember, I myself am with you every day until the close of the age.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

